deck_excerpt: Blind 2nd OTK game 1 then side into broken floodgates
deck_description:
This deck can beat tear and floo pretty consistently however spright and rikka are tough matchups. Exosister is probably our easiest matchup since we can avoid using the gy and easily OTK them or leave them on very low LP so they can't use any spell/traps they also lose to TCBOO. Heros lose hard to kaiju on DPE, just gotta play around spoly. Branded can screw us over with ra disciple but if they do the typical line with BiR we can steal MJ or bounce with alpha which puts them in a really bad position. Swordsoul can be tough if they have imperm/veiler to stop the OTK but if you leave a kaiju on their field they cant summon any tenyis to out zeus without commiting to a normal summon, also kaiju on baronne/sinister+stealing chixiao (lvl8) screws them over really hard.

I have found the best way to beat spright in games 2/3 is to go first and try to end on at least 2 floodgates, don't be afraid to blindly use the dangers for draw power, otherwise they will always be able to OTK you on turn 2. Ogre is a decent going 2nd card for floo and spright but it is rarely enough also spright plays around it with red. I don't run imperm/veiler because kaijus should be enough to deal with monsters, drawing a kaiju + imperm is usually not as good as drawing 2 kaijus and imperm can conflict with gizmek and it is 1 less lvl 8 for trade-in. Also CoH/mind con behave similar to imperm but gives us a body for a rank 8/zombie vampire.

Final Sigma is really hard for floo to out (they need to make underworld goddess), which is why I run ecclesia and it also nice to side in place of maju when I side in skill drain. 5 normal summons is too many for this deck since we have so much draw power (3 trade-in is effectively 6 upstarts), I ran 2 maju for a long time and would always brick.

Ash is good against every rogue deck and it can be used under shifter. Belle and called by are in the main because there are simply too many bystials in the format right now and 3 shifter is not enough, you only see it 1 in 3 games. Even if you only draw belle against tear, you could stop elf from bringing back diviner for baronne or merrli on your turn. Also being able to protect gizmek from the ishizu/bystials can be really good. Belle+shifter is insane because you negate called by and often times they use the bystial to dodge lethal and it forces them to wait an extra turn to out zeus with druis. Most decks rely on a monster reborn like effect as an interuption (BiR, expulsion, revolt, elf etc.). Called by is probably the best card against spright because you kaiju toad and when they go elf you use called by on either carrot or toad then safely resolve slumber, also called by on havnis can be really hard for tear to handle if you out cryme first. Any deck with elf I side out CoH, Mind con, and Alpha. Called by+shifter does usually suck going 2nd, but I think I still prefer it over adding another alpha/kaiju. Everyone is playing 6+ bystials so 5 GY hate is necessary. I have had games where I opened 2 shifter and the tear player bystial my gy to avoid lethal or out zeus just so I could shifter again next turn.

An argument could be made for necrovalley in place of summon limit, but I find 3shifter+calledby+belle+3dimfis is enough GY hate and summon limit is much better going first since it isn't telegraphed and works better with gizmek summon from GY. Also summon limit prevents zeus from hitting the field, so it is really good in combination with dimfis or TCBOO. Could also sub dimfis for necro but dimfis benefits us way more. I don't like macro cosmos because it is too slow, whereas dimfis/necro are still playable going 2nd into tear.

Kaijus/slumber/Alpha/mind con are all amazing against kashtira though, so I only see this deck getting better once kashtira becomes meta, only problem will be barrier statue which we out with bigfoot/gadarla/LS.

deck_excerpt: 8-axis with bystials and ecclesia for synchro plays
deck_description:
8-axis deck that abuses Lava Golem and Bystials. IMO deep sea diva is still better across matchups since it more easily OTKs but this deck has some advantages when facing tear and spright exclusively. You could tech in spoly/albaz but it just isn't that great in this meta. The biggest synergy with 8-axis is we can search schwarzschild off magna instead of lubellion which is decent if we happen to also have ecclesia because we can make baronne and a rank 8 pretty easily. Sauge+druis is pretty nuts, 1 banish+ 1 pop+1 send and we get a lvl 8 out of it. Ecclesia + Sauge + Magna gets us 3 lvl 8s (schwarz, iris, sauge) and magna or 2 lvl 8s and baronne. Magna search druis with a bunch of lvl 8s in hand makes it pretty easy to setup a rank 6 with draglubion for 15k numeron dragon, or just wipe their field with pain gainer and atk with 4k seven sins + 5k from the bystials. TCBOO can hurt since we have so many dragons and ecclesia cant summon iris under TCBOO without albaz in deck.

Just updated for ne banlist and kashtira, lava golem is insane against kash as are change of heart/mind con. Schwarzschild and alpha are great into fenrir since they do not trigger. Might consider ogre in main deck as fodder for bystial and counter adventure engine. Zeroboros I threw in last minute for scenarios I am forced to CoH a link monster and need a good payoff also summoning it against kash as alternative to a zeus wipe.
Just a very evil deck.  This is not good (in every sense of that phrase).

deck_excerpt: edit to fait-sc's punk reptile lockdown deck

deck_description:
Originally, I wasn't really feeling the Runick archetype. But when I found out that Runick is based on Norse mythology, particularly Odin and figures associated with him, I completely changed my tune. Thanks to the announcement that God of War: Ragnarok was coming out this year, I found myself getting invested in the Norse pantheon and Runick. 

 

This Runick Sky Striker deck is named "Freya the Runick Bride", because while Frigg is Odin's wife in Norse mythology, it is unclear whether or not Frigg and Freya are actually the same goddess. And they more or less touched upon this in God of War 4 and then Ragnarok. Also, "Frigg the Runick Bride" sounds really weird to say.

 

Anyways, this is a go-first deck, since Runick really doesn't care about your Battle Phase.

Ishizu's cards were the biggest mistake of 2022. Not only did they bring an already powerful deck to Tear 0 status, but as an engine, they manage to improve many other Graveyard-reliant decks. Fossils, Zombie World, Naturia, Burning Abyss, you name it. So it should be no surprise that these cards and Lightsworns go together like The Rick and Kevin Hart.

 

This deck is pretty decent whether you're going first or second, but the ideal is going first. You have some control options like Baronne or Bagooska. But its win condition against many decks is special summoning Archlord Kristya, which prevents both players from special summoning.Otherwise, your goal is to deck your opponent out or reduce their LP to 0. In addition, the deck uses both Exchange of the Spirit and Gravekeeper's Trap to potentially cripple your opponent's Graveyard.

deck_excerpt: My final tribute to Kazuki Takahashi (and my final deck for 2022)
deck_description:
Months ago, I found out that Kazuki Takahashi, the creator of Yu-Gi-Oh!, died saving 3 people from a riptide. So for his courage and bravery, I made a HERO deck in honor of him; and this will be the final deck I will submit in 2022. It contains both classic and modern HERO cards, mainly because of Elemental HERO Grandmerge, but also as a homage to Jaden Yuki.

 

Since Grandmerge is a battle-focused monster, it's ideal to go second, but thanks to the overall consistency of this archetype as well as Destiny HERO - Plasma, going first isn't too bad.

Fun non-meta Shaddoll Dogmatika deck featuring nostalgic cards like Magical Hats and Monster Reborn.

Magical Hats synergizes suprisingly well with Shaddolls, allowing for a pitch of fusion spells and traps which can be regained with El Shaddoll grave effects.

Monster reborn is a free monster, and Harpie's feather duster is backrow removal.

A deck I copied from Team NDL (youtube). A competent rank 4 toolbox revolving around level 4 dark monsters. Time thief alone is not very strong and prone to bricking. The deck incorporates raidraptors, rockets, and phantom knights as extenders. The phantom knights engine gives us strong back row negates with fog blade but is mostly useful for rank up magic spells and bardiche (4+1 engine super small).  

I reccomend watching the youtube video included to learn the combos more indepthly but I will loosley describe the 1 card combo.

Regulator->adjuster(1)+winder(2)->winder grabs retrograde,adjuster sends bezel ship->xyz raidraptor force strix->bezel ship gy effect to special summon self, force strix effect grabs singing lanius, special summon singing lanius->link into wise strix, wise strix effect ss raider's wing->xyz summon 2nd force strix and use effect discarding specifically raiders wing to grab strangle lanius-> wise strix procs to set and activate shave force by using the force strix in the gy to rankup into cyber dragon infinity (omni negate)-> use raider's wing in gy effect to detach material and ss self-> link force strix and wise strix into bardiche-> bardiche effect sends phantom knights silent boots to set rank up magic phantom knights-> gy effect silent boots to grab shade brigandine trap-> ss strangle lanius locking yourself into dark monsters-> stangle lanius field effects procs because cyber dragon infinty has an xyz card as material, ss singing lanius from grave-> xyz summon dark rebellion dragon into a place where bardiche points specifically using raiders wing so that it cannot be targetted (this will become the main boss beatstick), you can proc the pop effect if nessessary-> activate shade brigandine because you control no traps and then xyz summon time thief redoer-> set retrograde then pass turn.

An immaculate first turn 1 card combo although it is susceptible to negates (especially niburu). We run the rockets quick launch for this reasson in order to be an extender. The end board includes a cyber dragon infinity omni-negate as well as the effect to attack a face up attack monster as material on your turn (useful for bystials). a retrograde trap card that negates back row and attaches to redoer as material (trap only works with redoer ont the field). Redoer which can steal the top card of your opponents deck every standby phase, non-target spin an opponents card to the top of thier deck using the trap effect facilitated by shade brigadine, and banish self using monster as self portection so that you can survive the turn with the card at the vary least; these are quick effects btw, drawing power if you manage to steal spell card (trap is the best effect). as soon as possible use the rank up magic and banish your wise strix to go rank up dark rebellion dragon into dark requiem dragon triggering bardiche's pop effect if you ss into a pointed location. Dark requiem dragon has 3k attack and can negate monster effects upto 3x and this is not once per turn (stops board, grave yard, and hand effects/hand traps). dark requiem needs dark rebellion as material in order to use effects so discard that last. Raiders wing offers targetting protection so discard that 2nd last (situational if you rather avoid targeting over having effects. You should detach the other level 4 monster you used as material for dark rebelion first whether that is singing lanius or strangle lanius. On your turn you can use dark requiems effect to target the opponents monster bring its attack down to 0 while adding what was taken to requiems already high 3k damage, and this attack stays indefinetly. Dark reqium is your strongest and most important card. As much as i want to say redoer is the boss hes more like a support side piece compared to the reqium beatstick.

rokkets are the best extenders to play through ash blossoms or other negates. all 3 monsters are targets for quick launch. caliber can ss if you have wise strix or bardiche. recharger has good defence/ self protection and can also be a monster reborn in hand. tracer is my goto for my first quick launch use because the others have other effects in hand when you don't have a normal summon. Tracer is great for outing problem cards your opponent special summons to your field like the dinos token and resolving that quick effect gets you a free ss from deck to go into a dark rank 4 xyz. It is also great for outing the fog blade when you wantt it gone, or fly hack and salaman almiraj. Salaman great almiraj is an important extender and potential protection for the deck. Alot of the cards in the deck are chosen to be able to go into almiraj specifically all the hand traps, silent boots, radiers wing, singing lanius, caliber, recharger, regulator, and bezel ship. ***instead of 2 bezel ships, it was suppose to be 1 chronocorder too but the deck builder doesnt have it in inventory. bezel ship is a very important combo peice but is weak if it is in your hand. chronocorder is great in graveyard for followup and it can be a magic cylinder if your oppenent tries to focus attack with one large boss monster. they may be forced to skip battle phase. Salaman great alimirag can link off these monsters because their normal summon is a 1000 or less. The extender combo is having any of these listed cards in hand as well as a paralell exceed. You normal summon 1 of the viable cards, link into almiraj to proc exceeds and it will special summon itslef as a level 4 and ss another copy of itself onto the field also level 4 so that you can summon a rank 4. it is important not to clog the middle position or the right most position  because the first paralel exceeds needs almirajs arrow. An OTK package is included with raiders knights. if the opponents has alot of monsters on the field or you do and just need within 3000 to OTK you can use this option. xyz into rank 4 raiders knights with any 2 level 4 dark monsters. detach material to rankup into arc rebellion dragon. lasts 4 turns. it will gain bare damage for OTK. i prefer bagooska to stall with a brick hand, evilswarm knight is a great not once per turn book of moon to stop your opponent from linking. zeus is a great last resort for a sending black hole. Time thief is able to amass cards for to allow for the incredible zues double detach reuiring 4 matierials allowng zeus to play through a negate. If you have raiders wing as material you can make zeus untargetable. Flyback trap is great to get a specific material onto redoer or to disrupt your opponents GY, but is mostly useless its a perputua target (just scare your opponent into thinking it is mirror force lol). I think skull meister is way better than ghost belle and not once per turn but ghost belle is a target for almiraj. Instead of time thief hack I was suppose to run a 3rd ash blossom which is probably smarter but just to see more time thief cards I included it. It is a target for winder and its cool effect is to protect your xyz monsters from destruction the turn they are summoned. If you know your opponents has a monster destruction on hand you can use hack to protect and also it gives time thief redoer 300 attack for each material and allows it to attack directly. I think perpetua and double barrel are trash for the most part tbh better to put situational rank 4s. The 1 card combo can also rank up into ultimate falcon if you need to lets say your opponent destroys your board everything barring redoer and the rank up magic then you can rankup into falcon or arc rebellion using time thief when it comes back from banishment. play around with the hand traps maybe use allure of darkness for draw power, maybe you can get rid of the veillers and ghost belles for a radion dark kaiju package which can help alot with outing problem cards. Radion can be ss when even after you lock yourself into dark due to tracer or strangle lanius. Its 2800 attack so its not too crazy but it can also be something you use to up your opponents board attack so that you can increase your arc rebllion by 2800 or even open up the battle phase field w/ an attack positon monster. Be careful when locking yourself into dark becasue bagooska, exciton knight, and abyss dweller is no longer an option. Sadly, the paralell exceeds combo cannot give you the raiders knight OTK becasue it needs to dark monsters. 

Anyways lol if you actually read all this. This was just an adhd splurge but you'll probably know everything about this deck. pro tip if you do not have regulator but you do have winder and adjuster in hand you can normal winder search for start up and then use start up on adjuster to dumb bezel ship and still go full combo. This is the main reason we run that trash that is time thief start up. so regulator or winder+adjuster in hand can go full combo if not negated. Cool facts the archetype is based on a manga called chronos ruler. The time thiefs are pitted against the s-force archetype. Also all the girls in the art work (adjuster,startup,flyback,hack,perpetua) are all perpetua at different ages becasue the whole lore is about her creating a team to send to the past to save herself because is being targeted by other time travellers (kinda like the movie 'looper'). Anyways GG thank you for reading.

deck_excerpt: Bystial Ishizu Tearlaments / Las Vegas WCQ Regional 2nd Place
deck_description:
Category: Tournament Meta Deck

Tournament Meta Decks are current-level Meta Decks that are capable of going up against the best of the best. These are curated lists that cannot be uploaded by regular users.

Creator: Thaddeus Thomas "Bongham" Bingham

Tournament: Las Vegas WCQ Regional - December 17th 2022

Placement: 2nd Place

Fun Control Deck 

Give me feedback, this decklist has treated me well in this format

I came across this FTK combo through a Youtube video and have been doing lots of testing with it. This deck is what I've come ended up with that has the best consistency and has been allowing me to build a board if needed.

You will brick, DW bricks. It happens, this isn't a competitive deck but it can build boards if you want too (you either FTK or build a board, usually)

Here, I focus more on the Lvl8 to try extend the combo to use Coach King Giantrainer as I found with his build I couldn't quite get there. I'd always run out of momentum after using Number 15.

Fabled raven is handy, but it doesn't come up enough. It can't be searched through Snoww, so I took it out. I also don't run 3 Zalamanders as they can only be used once, so I find 2 is enough. 2 Lucent is also enough as you only need 2 for Number 6. Genta I play 2 of, instead of 3 as it's only got a single use. Blackwing - Zephyros can bounce an active copy of Gates back to your hand allowing it to be used again, plus brings a Lvl 4 onto the field. Because of this you could technically cut the 3rd copy of gates. But it doesn't hurt to open 1 or 2 copies as you usually will have enough resources in your starting hand for them.

One pin point is adding Ceruli to the hand from the GY. If you could accomplish this, it would add a little more consistency with Lucent to bring out Number 6. But I haven't found anything (or know of anything, please do let me know if you know something that would work, I would love to test it)

The combo & materials required to complete it, step by step

note: This is a general step by step, generally you should start with Number 60, but sometimes it doesn't work out that way, think ahead and try reach the correct materials. You have to ensure Number 60 is in the gy BEFORE Number 6 is summoned, or you'll miss the timing on the burn effect as it's an on summon effect. Most of the time, you should get the opponent down to 1400 LP. The final 1400 is the trickiest as you usually run out of momentum. But with enough luck and planning, you should be able to get there. GL!

(2 x Lvl 4 monsters)

1. Number 60: Dugares the Timeless,

  • Effect to Draw 2, Discard 1

 

If you need an additional Lv8 Summon, try go for Saryuja. It can SS one from hand

 

(2 x Lvl 6)

(this is what Lucent is used for, try to send Lucent using Ceruli Effect, it can summon the second copy required for this piece)

2. Number 6: Chronomaly Atlandis

  • Effect to Equip Dugares from gy, Eff to detach and remove Dugares then burn for half their life

 

(3 x Lvl 8 (Return these too the field using DW monsters, Danger's can be used also. Saryuja can SS one if needed))

3. Coach King Giantrainer

  • Effect to draw, then burn (if monster) x3 (800, 1600, 2400)

 

(2 x Monsters)

4. Geonator Transverser

  • Effect to swap Giantrainer (or Number 6, if you don't have Giantrainer) with their Ceruli

 

(2 x Lvl 8)

5. Number 15: Gimmick Puppet Giant Grinder,

  • Effect to destroy Giantrainer and burn for 1400

Victory!!

Credit to HaniTCG (Youtube) for the FTK Combo

This variant of swordsoul is meant to add more disruption/draw power with the runick cards on top of being able to do traditional swordsoul plays. Still testing ratios, the current version seems to be pretty consistent.

The following things could be changed if needed:

1. Play either two fountains, or terraforming with one fountain -> You can only search for one copy of the fountain with runick tip or with the one copy of Hugin.

2. Play two Hugin -> It was hard to decide what to remove from the extra deck, you could probably get away with removing a monk, but I felt I was too reliant on using all three in grind games.

3. Better side deck -> maybe darkrulers or other board breakers for going second, 

4. Possibly splash in some bystials? ->could replace the imperms since runick can make up for it. Haven't tested it, so wouldn't know how it would change the decks consistency, although it seems more sensible in this meta.

deck_excerpt: Updated version of Scrap Dinosaur Ogdoadic with new gameplay ideas
deck_description:
This is the most up-to-date version of the same deck that I've made before but with new card additions that improve existing synergies. He just isn't at full potential because he doesn't have Chaos Ruler, the Chaotic Magical Dragon anymore because the card was banned (we hope it comes back soon).

 

The idea behind this deck comes from the problem that the Dinosaur deck has after the Miscellaneousaurus limitation in the TCG: The deck manages to make the standard Dinosaur plays but doesn't have any good follow ups unless it uses weird cards that return Miscellaneousaurus to the GY, Deck or Hand.

 

With the addition of the Scrap Raptor engine, the deck continued to play with the same characteristic of having excellent starters that generate advantage through Babycerasaurus, which is the thematic card behind the archetype, but with a much larger and more versatile play ceiling.

 

Scrap engine allows you to improve access to extra deck monsters because it generates many more summons in addition to working very well as a starter also with Lost World or Miscellaneosaurus. And you only need to use 2 Scrap Raptor + 1 Scrap Chimera + Scrap Wyvern besides being able to make a full combo using only 1 Scrap Raptor so if you draw 1 of them it is still possible to play without problems.

 

To exemplify Scrap Dinosaur's combos, this deck profile of mine shows all the possible moves to use these engines efficiently: Scrap Dinosaur Jul21 Format

https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/scrap-dinosaur-jul21-format-190121

 

In the same way, I believe that using the Ogdoadic brings a new dynamic where you no longer lose to a hand trap in the Normal Summon, increases the options of plays in the first turn and even returns the follow up Miscellaneousaurus to the GY along with the Ogdoadic themselves which are follow up in the GY.

 

And I learned very early that when playing Dinosaur it's no use trying to make beautiful passing moves with Synchro Borreload Savage monsters + Link-4 Apollousa + Abyss Dweller etc that are combos that lose for all hand traps and many don't even have follow up which means that if the opponent uses a Dark Ruler No More and cleans your field you lose. So the intention is to do the basics of the deck which is to access XYZ monsters plus Follow Ups and some LINK-2 like I:P Masquerena or Spright Elf already guarantee an excellent end board.

 

This is the most creative deck I've ever made in the game and it's not a competitive deck because it has several problems when it goes first or second, whether it's not being able to open the best combinations of cards or the fact that there's no room for tech cards. Especially because easy to use cards that automatically give you an advantage are the best cards in the game. This is the safest way to play a game like Yugioh, it's much better to make a simpler move, weaker but much more efficient than a much more powerful move that has several weaknesses.

 

Now I'm going straight to the subject of hand tests that I did in this version that I already make it clear that they are not done in a didactic way because many plays I return or change the extra deck card that I do among other details but that by themselves manage to convey the idea base behind the deck.

 

Even in the previous version of the deck that I had already made a while ago, I have almost 30 combos that are still valid in this version (apart from the parts involving Chaos Ruler): Scrap Dino Ogdoadic Dec21 Format

https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/scrap-dino-ogdoadic-dec21-format-232240

 

So after seeing this other deck profile you can continue with Test Hands with the excellent Spright Elf but without the absurd Chaos Ruler:

Test hand 1 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45442028

Fossil Dig(Oviraptor) + Miscellaneousaurus + Giant Rex + Nauya + Aron

End Board: Tyranno + Dolkka + Number 38: Harbinger + Spright Elf + Babycerasaurus

 

Test Hand 2 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45438981

Miscellaneosaurus + Babycerasaurus Standard Combo

End Board: Tyranno + Dolkka + Number 38: Harbinger + Spright Elf + Babycerasaurus

 

Test Hand 3 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45438783

Combo example of Lost World + Dino Wrestling since you tried to play with the Ogdoadic and ended up taking Bystial and the opponent has more monsters than you.

In this example I did with the person being smart to ban Keurse. I:P Masquerena was also able to do it but I put Tyranno in the wrong monster zone which means you have to pay close attention to spamming monsters.

 

Test Hand 4 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45438473

Combo Lost World + Scrap Raptor: Could have waited to use Miscellaneousaurus eff only after using Oviraptor's second eff and making Evolzar Dolkka to throw around D.D. Crow.

Do I:P Masquerena since you can't do any RANK-4 in this example if you choose to play safe by doing Dolkka.

End Board: Tyranno + Dolkka + I:P Masquerena + Spright Elf + Babycerasaurus

(Note: Wyvern is summoned because the opponent controls monsters)

 

Test Hand 5 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45438396

Combo: (Snake Rain + Discard) + (Archosaur + Tyranno)

End Board: (Tyranno + Linkuriboh) + (I:P Masquerena + Keurse)

 

Test Hand 6 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45438037

FULL DECK COMBO: (Oviraptor + Babycerasaurus) + (Snake Rain + Discard)

As you already have both engines able to play independently so you can simply Abyss Dweller instead of Feral Imps and then activate Double Evolution Pill and make Spright Elf and bring Babycerasaurus that will be Keurse's tribute to play Ogdoadic.

End Board: Tyranno + Dolkka + Dweller + Number 38: Harbinger + Spright Elf + Babycerasaurus

 

Test Hand 7 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45598284

Combo: (Scrap Raptor + Miscellaneousaurus) + Nauya

End Board: Tyranno + I:P Masquerena + Iron

 

Test Hand 8 - https://www.duelingbook.com/replay?id=813757-45598064

Combo: (Nunu + Oviraptor + Oviraptor) = Combo Throw Around Hand Traps

End Board: Tyranno + Linkuriboh + I:P Masquerena + Iron

 

Points to pay attention to:

The amount of monster zones available because there are some combinations of cards that generate 2 monsters in the main monster zone so always be aware of this so as not to lose summons for nothing. Another very important point about these card combinations is that they always keep the deck's advantage as making XYZ Monsters and LINK Monsters has become very good because the cost is always replaced with other card combinations.

Combination 1 = Double Evolution Pill + Giant Rex = Tyranno + Giant Rex /

Combination 2 = Scrap Raptor plus any other monster on the field by itself is a 2 Link for free while interacting with the opponent among other really cool synergies.

Combination 3 = Keurse tribute Feral Imps = Keurse + Nauya with the possibility of Water Lily summoning happening.

Not counting when there was Chaos Ruler which also means more summons for free every turn making it possible to do I:P Masquerena.

Pay attention to when you want to do I:P Masquerena too because the Spright Elf's arrows might be all busy. And also pay attention in case you manage to leave a Scrap Raptor in the deck if you can play using only 1 of it, because since there are already few Dinosaur monsters in the deck, keeping that second Scrap Raptor is not bad most of the time and in the worst case you can add it with Oviraptor to be the Knightmare Unicorn discard made with I:P Masquerena.

 

Synergies:

Always be aware when using Aleirtt because you have to make sure you have Reptile banned and you have the options of Nauya and Nunu who are banned when they are special by Keurse or by themselves in the case of Nunu. You also have the option to banish a Reptile with the Double Evolution Pill and also in that same thinking you can use Bystial for that too.

Excellent synergy is between Scrap Wyvern and Spright Elf because before you went from Wyvern + Giant Rex and now you do it and that way you can reborn Babycerasaurus on your turn which becomes an excellent follow up on the opponent's turn to be destroyed with Tyranno and bring Oviraptor that adds another Tyranno to the hand and in this process he protects Tyranno and Dolkka from being targeted by the opponent's cards making them much better boss monsters which is something that previously needed the Lost World field to achieve.

And on the opponent's turn, the Spright Elf simply reborns the Scrap Wyvern again, which means that if he survives on your next turn, you can easily use his effect and reborn the Scrap Raptor and do the Borreload Savage, guaranteeing your victory. That is, this insane Link-2 is perfect in the deck working as a follow up, protection both by it and by triggering Lost World every turn and interaction with the opponent. Only you should remember that Spright Elf cannot be used as a link material the turn it is summoned.

 

What I noticed in the duels:

Crucial error: Follow Up to add to the hand at the end of combos or during the opponent's turn with Oviraptor will always be Tyranno, even because it is the main win condition of the deck and the card that has the most power to take control of the match for you by clearing the field so the opponent will do everything to take him out. And I noticed that Spright only takes him out using Spright Smasher and Bystial Druiswurm is another option, so always add another Tyranno to your hand whenever possible.

The Bystial cards are not good against my Dinosaur deck but they are excellent against the Ogdoadic cards so you will find it very difficult to play this part of the deck in many games.

Without Mystic Mine many matches don't need to worry about backrow but the more backrow hate you have available on the side deck the better it will be.

The two engines are very good at complementing each other to avoid one being stopped and you end up with nothing, but against the best decks released in recent times which are Spright and Tearlaments along with Kashtira and Bystial cards the deck has proven itself suffer a lot from power creep mainly since it no longer has access to one of the best extra deck cards which is Chaos Ruler, the Chaotic Magical Dragon.

 

Disregard the side deck because they are just examples of cards you can use in the extra deck or main deck. The first main deck cards I would consider pulling out are World Dino Wrestling and Set Rotation.

 

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
A Bakura deck made for fans who like the classic but with a little of modernity.

Basic aim of this deck is just to summon big fusions boosted by power bond. 

Main combo is: Cyber dragon core + Cyber dragon + Any spell:

Normal summon core. Search Cyberdark realm. Activate realm and search and then normal summon Cyberdark Chimera. Use Chimera effect to add powerbond. Now link Core and Chimera into Cyber dragon Sieger. Since Chimera's effect to turn any fusion into a pseudo powerbond, is active even if it leaves the field; activate power bond and fuse the Cyber dragon and Cyber dragon core into whatever fusion is best for what situation (most of the time it will be Rampage Dragon). If you fusion summon rampage dragon, you can destroy up to two spells and traps and also can send two cyber dragon monsters to the grave for additional attacks on that turn. If you do, send exactly Core and Herz to the grave so you can have follow up plays on the next turn; in case your 6300 atk fusion that can attack 3 times somehow doesn't otk.

deck_excerpt: Updated version of Utopia deck with new XYZ support
deck_description:
This is the version I decided to do about the last XYZ monster of Utopia's archetype = Number 39: Utopia Rising

 

To know in full about how the deck works today, I recommend the article I've done previously, which I leave below: Utopia Master Duel Feb22

https://ygoprodeck.com/deck/utopia-master-duel-feb22-250713

 

So, continuing with this change in the extra deck, I'll discuss the use of this card in the deck:

 

Number 39: Utopia Rising gives Utopia decks a recovery option and could continue combos if you get Nibiru, the Primal Being or any other board wipe.

 

* Ideas on using Utopia Rising in Grind Game:

Reborn of Number 39: Utopia "Original" transferring the materials to it and over Utopia Rising do S39: Utopia the Lightning and go to the battle phase to attack and use the combo of Utopia and Double or Nothing! just because you won't have another chance after using it and in Main Phase 2 doing AA-ZEUS over 39: Utopia with 2 Material. But you can also choose not to use Utopia's effect if you want to have 3 materials on AA-ZEUS to put pressure on your opponent if you destroy another one of the cards you control.

 

The same goes for if you made the Ultimate LEO Utopia Ray and the opponent dealt with it and is now in the GY because if you still have the ZW - Lightning Blade in the Deck it will be your main win condition in the grind game for negating effects of monsters every turn while halving their ATK.

 

A very cool point is the opponent using Nibiru, the Primal Being in the summon of Number 99: Utopia Dragonar and you in the following turn give him Reborn and bring LEO Utopia for example. It's solid applications for this card to help the deck establish the field after losing it on the opponent's turn or being stopped by hand traps.

 

Another very interesting application is if you take Nibiru in Number F0: Utopic Future and you bring it back to the field and do Number F0: Utopic Draco Future on top. This line of play I've seen players use on turn 1 during the deck combo so you can do 2 F0: Utopic Draco Future on the end board but I consider this a wrong use of 39: Utopia Rising since the standard play of the deck is already make several monster negates because the combination of LEO Utopia and ZW - Pegasus is 2 Monster Negates and with the first F0: Utopic Draco Future that number increases to 3 which means making a redundant move.

 

The best use of Number 39: Utopia Rising in the deck I see it as being Follow Up in grind games because the Utopia deck is not made for multi-turn play as you go all-or-nothing when making an overwhelming end board with many monster negates among other interactions very difficult to be broken via the opponent's deck engine.

 

Soon the deck has limitations in the sense of few follow ups and few options of extra deck moves in the return turn due to the use of more than half of the Extra deck to build moves of turn 1. This is where Number 39: Utopia Rising shines to help you to have more control of the game when you lose your established field.

 

Finally, other changes I made to my Utopia deck:

Using ZW - Lightning Blade instead of ZW - Tornado Bringer proved to be much better because Ultimate Leo Utopia Ray does not interact with the opponent if it is not equipped with a ZW monster and if the opponent uses a Lightning Storm for example you practically lose two negates of monsters including the one from ZW - Pegasus Twin Saber. So this destruction protection proved to be better during games than target protection.

 

Another main change was using Number 92: Heart-eartH Dragon instead of Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy since even though it is excellent to negate spells on the opponent's turn, Number 92 is able to be used by surprise in the End Phase to banish all opponent's set cards which means winning games against trap decks.

And since decks that use a lot of spells are usually combo decks that need to resolve a lot of monster effects and the deck alone already ends the combo with at least 2 more monster negates so I see it being a great choice to opt for Number 92 instead of Number 38.

 

And another excellent use of Number 99: Utopia Dragonar on the opponent's turn besides bringing Number 92 is using it to bring Number 41: Bagooska the Terribly Tired Tapir which becomes a great floodgate against several decks that will hurt the turn a lot of them and that even making your monsters also cannot activate effects you will still have the ZW - Pegasus Twin Saber to negate monster effects and the Numbers Protection or any hand trap to stop any other move he tries to make.

 

Now between the synergy of Number 99: Utopia Dragonar with Number 39: Utopia Rising is that you can use Utopia Dragonar to bring Rising that will reborn another Number XYZ from GY like Number F0: Utopic Draco Future among others and even later it may bring Number 39 back. So, there is an excellent option of cards to give Reborn and recover his win condition again to the field since in addition to giving Reborn he transfers his own xyz materials.

 

That's why this small change in the Utopia deck greatly improves the grind game and makes it possible to easily establish your field to take control of the game.

 

Disregard the side deck, they are just card options that you can test.

deck_excerpt: Just like Branded Despia, Predaplant offers a interesting and unique gameplay - Representing the pinnacle of combo fusion summoning!
deck_description:
Predaplant Branded serve as Branded Despia's little sibling living in it's shadow. While Branded Despia can relies on Mighty, easy-to-summon beatsticks and resource advantage, Predaplant Branded creates multi-negate boards that most decks would have great difficulty breaking. 

On top of that, Predaplant can search out ANY fusion spell! Missing Branded Fusion in your hand? Search for it! Want that pesky 1-of Instant Fusion spell for Winda? Search for it! Want to break your opponen'ts board with Super Poly? Search for it!

While arguably slightly weaker and less consistent than it's mighty meta friend Branded Despia, Predaplant offers a interesting and unique gameplay - Representing the pinnacle of combo fusion summoning!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

 

ARCHETYPES, ENGINES AND DECKBUILDING

This deck is synergistic combination of fusion focused archetypes to support the main Predaplant strategy. The Branded and Edge Imp engine add additional consistency, power and starters. 

  • Forming the deck's core strategy, Predaplant cards consist of 11 cards.

3 Byblisp, 2 Chlamydosundew, 1 Orphys Scorpio, 1 Darlingtonia Cobra, 1 Bufolicula, 1 Triantis, 1 Instant Fusion and 1 Staysailor Romarin. In the Extra Deck there are 1 Ambulomelides, 2 Dragostapelia, 1 Triphyoverutum, 1 Starving Venom Predapower Fusion Dragon and 1 Starving Venom Fusion Dragon. 

  • Assisting the main strategy, the Branded/Despia cards in the Main Deck consist of 13 cards:

2 Tragedy, 2 Aluber, 1 Ad Libitum, 3 Branded Fusion, 2 Branded Opening, 1 Branded Banishment and 1 Branded in Red. In the Extra Deck there are 2 Albion, 2 Lubellion, 1 Mirrorjade and 1 Masquerade.

  • Facilitating additional fusion plays and hand advantage for discards, the Edge Imp engine in the maindeck consists of 8 cards:

3 Frightfur Patchwork, 3 Edge Imp Chain and 2 Polymerization. 

  • The boardbreaker cards and staples consist of 8 cards:

2 Super Polymerization (and it's Extra Deck targets), 2 Evenly Matched and 1 Harpie's Feather Duster. Fairy Tail Snow serves as an additional light target/discard fodder for Branded Fusion. 1 Foolish Burial and 2 Called By the Grave help your plays plays get through handtraps.

COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN

Predaplant Branded has a very similar gameplan to a pure Branded deck. While Pure Branded maintains hand advantage and easily generates giant beatsticks, Predaplant takes that a step further. Predaplant makes bigger boards that are more difficult to break, and it trades Banishment/Destruction interruption for straight up monster/omni negates. A multi-negate Predaplant board is created through a non-linear combo which can somewhat play through interruption. (Ash on Branded Fusion still stops you cold however!)

Generally, no matter what hand, most Predaplant Branded combo starts with the following steps: 

 

  1. Gain access to Branded Fusion. (Predaplant can search the card from deck by Orphys Scorpio, normal summoned or summoned from deck by Ambulomelides).
  2. Activate Branded Fusion for Albion, sending Albaz + Staysailor. 
  3. CL1 Staysailor to send Byblisp from deck, CL2 Albion to fuse for Lubellion, banishing a dark monster and Albaz from field/GY. 
  4. CL1 Byblisp to search for either Orphys Scorpio (If you can't normal summoned yet) or Bufolicula (additional fusion summon), CL2 Lubellion to fuse for either Mirrorjade (interruption) or Ambulomelides (more resources). 
  5. Depending on your hand, the monsters on your field and GY set-up, you fuse the rest of the monsters in your field and hand to summon Predaplant boss monsters. The end result field varies by situation/hand, but its usually any combination of Mirrorjade, Dragostapelia, Triphyoverutum, Starving Venom Fusion Dragon and a set Spell/Trap Fusion interruption like Super Poly, Branded in Red and Branded Banishment.
  • If you already have Bufolicula in your hand, it is ideal to search Triantis with Ambulomelides. Fusing Bufolicula + Triantis + 1 more dark monster on the field to create Triphyoverutum distributes Predaplant counters on the field raising up Triphyoverutum attack to astronomical levels for an OTK. 
  • If you have multiple leftover fusion monsters on field (Albion, Lubellion, Ambulomelides, Mudragon, Chimera), they are ideal material for Predaplant Dragostapelia and Starving Venom Fusion Dragon.

If you want more advanced and detailed combo guides on Predaplant Branded, I highly suggest you check out Yacine656's guide on Predaplant Branded.

 

 

The board your opponent will have to deal with will have an omni-negate, Extra Deck summon negate, monster negate and set spell/trap interruption. Your hand and GY should also have enough follow-up for OTK next turn, should your board be cleared by your opponent. 

 

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

 

 

GENERAL TIPS

 

  • Ash Blossom on Branded Fusion still stops your mainline combo in its tracks! Try to bait out the Ash/Interruption as much as possible - then use Branded Fusion. 
  • In order for Starving Venom Predapower Fusion Dragon's omni-negate to be live, it needs a monster on field with a predator counter. Predator counters are distributed by using Triantis as fusion material. Or even better, use Dragostapelia to give your opponent's monster a predator counter, then tribute it as cost!
  • There are 8 flex spots in this deck where staples are used. My preferred strategy in Masterduel's Bo1 format is using board breakers so I can play the game. These 8 flex spots can be filled with any card you like however, like handtraps such as Maxx "C" or draw cards like Allure of Darkness. 
  • If you are going first and have access to Instant Fusion (Remember, Orphys Scorpio and Darlington Cobra searches any fusion card) + Branded Opening, you can summon Winda and effectively bypass Instant Fusion's self-destruct effect by having your spent Branded Opening in the GY!
  • This deck has many routes to the same endboard result. One combo guide cannot do the complexity of this deck justice. I highly recommend practicing for yourself how this deck works and you'll see what I mean!

 

CONCLUDING COMMENTARY

Has your Branded deck become a bit stale with overuse the past couple months? Has the consistency hits from the banlist lower the power level for your Branded deck? If you wanna spice up your Branded deck with a cool set of ferocious eldritch mutated plants, Predaplant is the deck for you!

Trading power and resources for negates and board presence, Predaplant offers its own unique flavour of fusion summoning with Branded cards. Hope you fusion enthusiasts have as much with this deck as I do!

GLHF Duelists!

Small World is cracked in this build.

2. Laolao > Lili > Lulu

5. Nyannyan > Ash > Lulu

deck_description:
A Slifer deck built around a combination of the Lair of Darkness and Virus traps.

It is designed to be quite affordable. The most pricey cards of the deck are Lord of the Heavenly Prison and Leviair the Sea Dragon .

Side deck shows some other options for the deck.

Main Mechanic

The main mechanic of this deck consists in destroying your opponent's useful cards (spells and monsters) and bringing Slifer the Sky Dragon out from the grave with The Revived Sky God and waging a powerful direct attack with a hand full of cards.

Use Lair of Darkness and tribute you opponent's monsters to activate your virus cards such as Eradicator Epidemic Virus.

Combos

Activate The Revived Sky God with the Virus effects active during the end phase of your opponent to prevent them from filling their hand, and to draw up to 6 cards. When Slifer goes to your grave, banish The Revived Sky God to add Monster Reborn to your hand. Next turn, revive Slifer using Monster Reborn to attack with a whooping 7000 ATK. Thunderforce Attack can clear the field anytime, letting your opponent wide open for an attack.

If you send Slifer to the grave with Peaceful Burial and special summon it with The Revived Sky God in the same turn, Slifer will stay on the field by the end of the turn since Peaceful Burial prevents it from activating its effects (but it does not negate them, so Slifer will still have 6000 ATK)

Absolute King Back Jack is useful for setting more trap cards and controlling the top of your deck. Bring it out with One for One and send it to the grave with Linkuriboh. Place a trap on top of your deck and set it during your opponent's turn by Back Jack's effect. It can be activated right away. Absolute King Back Jack can be recycled with Leviair the Sea Dragon.

Summon Tour Guide From the Underworld and bring out Sangan, to link summon Beat Cop from the Underworld. With her ability and Lair of Darkness on the field, you can tribute an opponent's monster to set a patrol counter on your field spell, thus protecting it. Tour Guide can also be used to bring out Leviair the Sea Dragon.

Dark Sacrifice can protect your cards from destruction and send Absolute King Back Jack to the grave, thus triggering its effect.

Lord of the Heavenly Prison also protects your set traps, and helps setting more traps while being a tribute target for Grinning Grave Virus. You can also use it to XYZ summon a rank 10 monster such as Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Gustav Max and start dealing some damage.

Ahrima, the Wicked Warden's ability allows you to search for the LoD, and can also bring out your Lord of the Heavenly Prison.

The ladies of lament such as Lilith, Lady of Lament are here for further trap support while feeding the LoD mechanic for more tokens. Tokens can then be used a link materials.

Every normal trap in the deck have at least one copy to work with Trap Trick. Trap trick gets you the trap you need and allows you to activate it right away.

Other Possibilities

Kuribandit can be used to fill your graveyard by tributing itself, adding a spell or trap card to your hand and possibly sending Absolute King Back Jack or Slifer the Sky Dragon to your grave. It'll leave a token behind if LoD is active.

Tour Bus From the Underworld can be used together with Tour Guide to annoy decks relying on sending specific cards in their grave.

Card Destruction can send your egyptian god or absolute king back jack from the hand to the grave.

Horn of Heaven works well with LoD since it negates a summoning by tributing one monster.

Chaos Burst is here to destroy monsters and deal damage.

Darklight can wipe out your opponent's field.

Dark Spirit Art - Greed can help you draw and can't get negated if you destroyed your opponent's spell cards with Eradicator Epidemic Virus.

Another option is to add Heavy Storm Duster in your deck to destroy annoying field spells or traps that would lock your game.

Note

This deck isn't fully optimized since I focused on making it affordable. The side deck could be improved, based on how much you are willing to spend and what you already have.

Take care ♥

deck_excerpt: Burn your opponent with goat tokens!
deck_description:
This deck aims to utilize Amazon Archer's effect to burn your opponent for big damage using your goat tokens.

Big Shield Gardna is an awesome card in burn decks as its ability to eat NoC is very handy. Des Koala is a staple in burn decks as well, as are the jars and Sangan. We'll just be running (2) Amazon Archers as we don't want to see them in our opening hand. (2) Night Assailants provide handy removal, and (3) Giant Germ lets us burn our opponent and float more monsters. 

(3) Scapegoats are present to get them on the board as soon as possible, along with (3) Book of Moon. Running spells that can be chained to removal is extremely helpful. We also run Pot, Graceful, and MST.

The rest of the deck consists of the staple burn deck traps, and that will bring us to 40 cards! The side deck aims to replace most of your burn traps with burn spells, as your opponent is very likely to side into Royal Decree. Swap out your Night Assailants for Lava Golem, and your opponent will be put into quite a tight spot.

deck_excerpt: Unleash the power of chaos! A budget deck with Dark Magician, Blue-Eyes White Dragon and Chaos rituals.
deck_description:
A budget deck with Dark Magician, Blue-Eyes White Dragon and Chaos ritual monsters.

Main Mechanic

Bring out your normal monsters fast in order to use them as fusion, ritual or XYZ materials. Summon Dark Magician the Dragon Knight to protect your spells and traps and make it mostly invulnerable with Eternal Soul and Piercing the Darkness, while banishing and destroying cards with Dark Magic Attack, Dark Magical Circle and Magician of Chaos.

Combos

Thanks to Cosmo Brain or Fusion Deployment, you can easily special summon Dark Magician and Blue-Eyes White Dragon on your field from your deck. Cards like Piercing the Darkness or Dark Magical Circle make these summoning count, allowing to draw and banish cards. Illusion Magic and Summoner's Art can search for these same monsters, which can be used to summon Cosmo Brain. Eternal Soul can special summon Dark Magician once a turn.

Cosmo Brain can summon Dark Magician on the field by tributing an effect monster, and go for Ebon High Magician (more defensive) or Ebon Illusion Magician (more offensive).

Chronicle Magician summons itself when Dark Magician or Blue-Eyes White Dragon get on the field and give them a big ol' 2500/2500 boost until the end phase. Combined with Piercing the Darkness, you can easily deal at least 5000 points of damage with a single blow. Chronicle Magician can also be used to go for an easy rank 7 XYZ summoning.

Keeper of Dragon Magic allows you to search for Fusion Deployment, Magicalized Fusion or Polymerization. You can discard a fusion material like Dark Magician, Blue-Eyes White Dragon or Witch of the Black Forest from your hand to activate its effect, then summon it from the grave face-down. Keeper of Dragon Magic makes it much easier to fulfill the summoning conditions of Dark Magician the Dragon Knight.

/!\ Be careful: when using Keeper of Dragon Magic, you can't Link, XYZ or Synchro summon in the same turn. /!\

Dark Magician the Dragon Knight and Eternal Soul make for a great force together, since Eternal Soul make Dark Magicians unaffected by your opponent's effects and can resurrect Dark Magician the Dragon Knight any time. The Dragon Knight prevents your opponent from destroying or targeting your spells and traps. One of the main goals of this deck is to get a board with the Dragon Knight and Eternal Soul active. Piercing the Darkness complete this combo by making your Dragon Knight virtually invincible.

This combo would leave your opponent with a very few possibilities of breaking through : Kaijus, effects that banish/bounce traps without targeting, or this bad boy: Trap Eater.

Magician's Rod can search for any Dark Magician-related spell or trap (except for The Eye of Timaeus uuuuurgh). You can search for Magician's Salvation, activate it and set Eternal Soul directly from your deck. It can also search for Chaos Form or Secrets of Dark Magic to go for rituals or fusions.

You can easily bring out Blue-Eyes Chaos MAX Dragon or Magician of Black Chaos MAX by using Blue-Eyes White Dragon (most likely from your grave) with Chaos Form. Same goes with Magician of Chaos by using Dark Magician. Since Magician of Chaos's name is changed to "Dark Magician" on the field and in the grave, banishing a Dark Magician for its summoning is no big deal.

Magician of Chaos's powerful ability allows you to destroy a card on the field when a spell/trap is activated, making a good combo with Dark Magical Circle. Since its effect isn't a hard "once per turn", it can destroys itself to bring out a Chaos MAX from your hand, be special summoned back from the grave by Eternal Soul and activate its effect again to destroy another card on the field.

Witch of the Black Forest can search for Blue-Eyes Chaos MAX Dragon. Since Chaos MAX Dragon doesn't activate any effect, it doesn't suffer from the downside of the Witch's effect. She can also search for useful monsters for the next turn.

Lighten the Load is here to reduce the risk of bricking.

Magicalized Fusion works well as a late game changer. Fuse 5 spellcasters with different names to leash out Quintet Magician and destroy every card on your opponent's field, and go for a whoopin' 4500 of direct damage. Starving Venom Fusion Dragon can surprise your opponent with a quick fusion by Secrets of Dark Magic and destroy monsters as payback if Eternal Soul gets destroyed.

Master of Chaos is a walking danger who can banish every monster on your opponent's side of the field by tributing Blue-eyes and a dark monster.

Blue-Eyes Ultimate Dragon, Dark Magician Girl the Dragon Knight  and Musician King are here for summoning Blue-Eyes White Dragon, Dark Magician Girl and Witch of the Black Forest by the effect of Fusion Deployment or Keeper of Dragon Magic.

Notes

This deck isn't fully optimized and designed to be affordable. There are change suggestions in the side deck.

Take care ♥

Built off of Faith_SC's Timelord troll deck.

I've been climbing comfortably and having a lot of fun with this deck. As a relatively new player, it's nice to use a niche deck that can be relaxingly played into the ladder. The deck goes 2nd really well (which is great within the coin flip gamble of queueing up in Master Duel) and decks without skill cancellation tend to struggle against it.

As a new player I started with True Draco to have a any chance on ladder, and have since evolved the deck slightly with Eldlich. Eldlich gives True Draco a little more consistency- a possible 3500 eldlich on board (stronger than any possible draco) and another avenue of removal.
Big pile 'o' zombie synchroing. fairly self explanatory, exploit graveyard filling cards like the Ishizus. In-depth walkthrough in my video.

Eldlich brings an extra layer to Dragonmaid, I believe. While the typical Dragonmaid gameplan is core (cycle dragonmaids and utilize Sheou as powerful negater), Eldlich helps with board clearing and an added easy-to-cycle-in monster. 

 

Synergy:

- Laundry can dump Eldlich, Edlich traps, Dragonmaid Tidyings, and Noctovision dragons comfortably, and gives you a headstart on filling up your graveyard for the Dragonmaid cycle. 

- Noctovision is a great surprise negate from the GY. Get it in the GY by being hand-summon fodder with Changeover for Sheou, or it can dumped with Laundry Dragonmaid. 

- Eldlich's discard ability can be used with Changeover or Tidying.

deck_excerpt: Low-cost Krawler deck Penguin Soldier is farting around
deck_description:
A low-cost insect flip monsters deck that has a chance against stronger decks.

Swarm the field with Krawlers as your opponent tries to set their field / destroy your monsters. Despite being slow, Krawlers can break your opponent's momentum with World Legacy's Mind Meld or World Legacy Pawns combined with their own effects.

Get World Legacy's Mind Meld in your graveyard with Girsu, the Orcust Mekk-Knight or Foolish Burial Goods to special summon Deus X-Krawler quickly, the ace of the deck.

Waboku protects your Krawlers from battles, forcing your opponent to remove your monsters from the field, which activates the Krawlers' ability to swarm the field.

Dragonbite can bring out Penguin Brave ‑which protects your face-down monsters and searches for Penguin Soldier‑ or Underground Arachnid to remove strong monsters.

If you have money, add some Maxx "C". Since it's a level 2 EARTH insect, it can also be a target for World Legacy in Shadow and be used as material for your Krawler links.

Your main winning condition is to have X-Krawler Qualiark with a total of 6 Krawlers on your field to attack directly while locking your opponent's effetcs.

Notes: This deck is a personal favorite. It doesn't look strong at first and is more technical than it first appears, but it can do little wonders for so little price! ♥

deck_description:

Following that, having Labrynth on field guarantees that Sanguine will summon Eldlich. Ask any Master Duel player, if you play a broken deck that everyone hates, you're a garbage human being, but add an archetype that's less than stellar and it is immediately based. Ask any Branded Predaplant or Synchro Runick player and they'll agree.

deck_excerpt: There's a solution to every problem.
deck_description:
This deck is more lethal than it appears on paper. It can search, draw, destroy, swarm, negate, recycle, and beatstick. The point is to blitzkrieg your opponent and exhaust their negates. In other words, pressure them into making plays. Notable cards:

1. Blue-Eyes Jet Dragon - Special Summons itself via the easiest condition ever. Triggered by Alternative Dragon, Chaos Emperor, Raigeki, Feather Duster, and Crocodragon. This card carries. Play 2.

2. Triple Tactic Tasking - Searches 16 of 20 spells. Turns interruptions into pluses. Need I say more?

3. One Day Of Peace - Buys time if you brick. Forces opponent to go first. Gamechanging card (in case of emergency break glass).

4. Psychic End Punisher - Search Ash with Piri Reis Map. Synchro Ash + Level 8. Field removal that runs over problematic cards. This is your simplest OTK.

5. Number 23: Lancelot, Dark Knight Of The Underworld - Easy damage/removal. Direct attack grants instant access to Zeus. I've been running this for 6 years.

deck_excerpt: Zombie Synchro is challenging, rewarding and fun as hell to play.
deck_description:
Please add Deer Note, Konami.

It's been done a million times on ygopro and I'm here to add that one millionth and one deck listing to the mix. Zombie Synchro is not only heightened by the P.U.N.K. engine; it also is the coolest duel-archetype aesthtic in the game. The idea of cyber punk zombies is enough to realese endorphines upon the thought alone. The deck itself is brilliant. It imparts a variety to the game that is rarely seen in the average Master Duel match. This is because Zombie Synchro boasts a nonlinear combo game that is adaptable to a variety of situations your opponent can throw at you, making the deck have a high skill ceiling that requires the user to not only have a knowledge of each of their card's effects, but also a knowledge of the your opponent's cards as well. The challenge the deck provides will always lead to a feeling of superiority after besting your opponent in any Gold IV game.

Something that my deck listing delivers that other decks don't is a good selection of hand traps that makes this "Going First" deck have an easier time when you inevitably lose the coin flip. It also keeps the card count as close to 40 as possible while ensuring no part of either the Zombie or P.U.N.K. engine is weakend to save space. Most other Zombie decks (especially on MD Meta) will instead go for a 60 card deck and try to high roll with That Grass Looks Greener as a less than dependable strategy. This deck strives for consistency in the opening hand and is really what I want to preface most of all, because while it is a wonderful feeling when your deck gives you a godly hand that can lead to setting a Baronne, Balerdroch and a Zombie Dragon Lord on turn one, that feeling is muffled when you brick five games in a row before getting it. So 3 Banshees, 3 Zombie Worlds, and 3 Ze Amins. This will allow even your most abyssmal of hands to set up Zombie World and a tuner, the minimum you will want to do. From there, have fun, experiment, and learn the ins and outs of the deck because it is a maze of combinations and plays that is second only to D/D.

The most important thing I can say is learn when you are locked into Zombies because there are a fair amount of times where I could have gone for a great end board but I simply triggered my effects in the wrong order. Other than that, I can only reiterate that the deck provides a challenge that will put your skills as a duelist to the test and I sincerely hope you give the deck a try because it is the first deck to truly make me feel like I'm playing Yu-Gi-Oh.

As a P.S. to this literal essay (bless you if you've actually read this far) some youtube channels that can help you with your journey are TheAfroCain, MasterDuelCentral, and my personal favorite Redzero03. The deck really gave me something to feel proud about when playing the game because I always wanted to craft a combo deck that wasn't linear but actually required you to think about your next play. Which, don't get me wrong, there's nothing wrong with simple decks, I for one play Salamangreat all the time. But it gets boring. You don't have to use my listing, but I hope you give Zombie Synchro a try and that the deck gives you that same feeling of excitement it gave me.

deck_excerpt: Music for your ears but not your opponent
deck_description:
So after some play testing but this is not final yet, the deck now has full accessibility to link summon & synchro summon, you may adjust the ratio of the pendulum magicians to your liking. Based on playtesting, the deck RARELY bricks but that is not a 100% guarentee it will never happen. So continue switching handtraps as you see to your liking, this will serve just as a BASE deck build

FAQ
1. Why not put call by the grave in the main deck?
This is dependent on your area if they're playing Maxx C or Effect Veiler (Effect Veiler is the greatest threat, as its not once per turn), I do recommened you put them in cause if either one triggers, you're in for an out of hand situation unless you OTK or have a full negate board while pendulum summoning. Take note this deck CORE principle is to pendulum swarm and link as much as you can with or without the 2 negates

2. Have you considered Kurikara Divinecarnate?
Yes, if you thought of not letting monster effects run free during your turn

3. Is it necessary for that Antihuman Meta Me Psy A to be in the deck?
Scale of 0 with banish anything that goes into the GY except monsters when used as a scale, you can bully those magic spammy decks or trap deck with it

3. Why no XYZ like Odd Eyes Absolute Dragon?
I did consider it but if you were to use that, then might as well add on Odd Eyes Pendulumgraph for maximum usage.

4. Why not using Odd Eyes Pendulumgraph, it has a good negate magic effect when u have an empty scale?

It's underutilizing pendulumgraph without the other odd eyes dragons, as you do get a bonus Odd Eyes summon with it.
I added wida to the deck and some shaddoll monsters to ult beatriz with the tearla putting winda on the field

Fun deck where you can special summon something every round a play around with combinations. Its main beast is Malicious Bane but you can summon other fun combinatios with 10k+ ATK. Also has many negates and you cant bait summon for days and still get a nice board out at the end.

Its very good and can beat many opponents but if they have really meta decks with countless negates and board wipes then at some point you will just loose. Main weakness i noticed is Red Eyes Dark Dragon which can be beaten if you get Malicious Bane out, put him in DEF position and spam its abillity if they have other monsters and then wait for Dark Ruler No More (idr if it works?)

Theres hardly any brick chances, like 95% of times you wont brick or even more.

And some cards are optional like Neos which i dont need to use, its just for fun surprises, you can remove or exchange Woodsman for Blazeman (idk really which one is better or if they are even needed + their use is situational), Dark Ruler No More is also optional and situation based, Dian is there for rare situations with only Solid Soldier or i guess now Woodsman on the board with Mask Change, Adoration almost never used, as there are always better options, its only here to fill out the ED and maybe a last reserve and it could be replaced with other card you prefer like Escuriado, Divine Wind is there for fun for card draw but i never use it as there are better options but it can be used for variety plays and it replaced Blast which was kinda used for backrow, kinda same with Acid. You could maybe add/exchange Parallel World Fusion, Monster Rebord or add one Polymerization and Miracle Fusion

This series is too resource-intensive, but I love it.

Feedback is always welcome.

This decklist is mostly a baseline for anyone looking to build a Labrynth deck. It is not perfect and shall be tweaked at a later date. Labrynth is a great deck for anyone looking to shut down an opponent physically (In the Labrynth :D lol) and mentally. As we are waiting for one of the best cards in this deck to be released in the TCG, "Big Welcome Labrynth," we can substitute this for some Ice Dragon's Prison, an extra Torrential Tribute, or make Ghastly Glitch a 3 of. You can also cut the furnitures to add some additional traps but they help with getting Back Jack to the grave (Don't be afraid to discard mosters if you have Labrynth Labrinth up. We can Summon them back) as well as being a set for Welcome Labrynth and can bait negates like everyone's favorite card ASH BLOSSOM!!! Don't forget that you can use the field spell + Compulsory Evacuation Device to do massive damage on your Battle Phase by sending a monster that has already battled back to the hand and re-summoning it from the had for a double attack. With this combo we can easily OTK with only 2 monsters.

Minha versão do branded dark magician,focado em fusão usando a engine de branded para fazer o deck rodar mais ainda.

Os boss do deck seriam o mirrorjade e o dragoon porém as outras fusões de mago negro podem ser bem úteis dependendo da ocasião.

Alguns Pontos sobre o deck:

- a ecclesia incrível é um extender pro deck pois ela entra por special e pode invocar o albaz direto do deck o que já faz fusão usando cards do oponente.

- A cartesia além de entrar por special com um caído de albaz no campo ou cemitério permite fazer fusão usando cards do campo ou da mão,e no final do turno ela ainda volta do cemitério pra mão, além de ser mago podendo ser usado pra fazer o quinteto.

- A engine do Branded além de ajudar a fazer o dragoon permite recuperar cartas banidas com o lubelion que era um grande defeito do deck quando os magos negros são banidos,fora que o mirrorjade é insano de forte kkkk.

Sobre algumas spells do deck

- Allure of the darkness é uma spell de compra que não gera tantos problemas já que o monstro banido pode ser recuperado com efeito do lubelion,cartas como pote da extravagância e pote da prosperidade são ótimas opções porém acabam banindo seu extra deck de forma que não dá pra recuperar.

- Piercing the darkness é uma ótima carta pois além de dar uma draw sempre que o mago negro for invocado com ela ativada,ainda permite somar o ataque do oponente no seu e ganhar a troca na fase de batalha.

- Implantar fusão é uma ótima carta tanto para começar revelando uma fusão do extra deck dando special do caído de arbaz direto do deck e já dando efeito ou você pode trazer o red eyes Black dragon ou o mago negro direto do deck para fazer o dragoon ou as outras fusões de mago negro.

- Fusão dos olhos vermelhos é a carta quase perfeita para fazer o dragoon, é a carta que liga direto no dragoon porém agora com a engine de branded e o lubelion voltando os matérias pro deck permite usar uma segunda ou até terceira a spell de fusão.

- Super polimerização é a carta pra quebrar o campo do oponente, já que nessa build não estou utilizando handtraps como ash ou veiler que são comuns nos decks, a super poly aparece como uma das interações para remover monstros do oponente e ainda criar um monstro do seu lado do campo. Além dos alvos de super poly que estão no extra deck a quimera no side serve perfeitamente para lidar com decks de cyberso, o garura pode ser adicionado no side como um dos alvos da super poly pois é muito bom e gera uma draw ainda.

- Expulsão do marcado junto com o servo de rá é uma ótima maneira de travar o oponente de forma com que ele consiga invocar somente um dos deuses egípcios porém essa jogada é um pouco lenta e custosa já que para ativar a expulsão do marcado precisa tributar uma fusão em campo.

deck_description:
Why 4 onomat monsters? - No, i have in total 8 onomat monsters and 1 pot of prosperity.  

The strongest cards are Ascended/Armed with utopia double because they trigger chain link that can make cards such as veiller useless.

I have Dragonic Ray in case utopia double is negated, in that case i special summon him in opponent turn by utopia double quick eff.

Why i don't play draco? It's wasting space and my board can be: Dragonar + Draco + leo equiped + num 38

Without draco my board is: Dragonar + leo equiped + num 38 + Dweller. It's stronger board and the strategy to make it is safer, so i don't need draco.

 

important: Zs utopic sage is high risk to be played because is target for negate, so use it in powerful combos that can make a good board even if he is negated.

Important: Onomatopaira + Onomatopickup or similar 2 card combos that can lead you to get to the 3 unique onomat monsters in hand, after you normal summon Utopic Onomatopoeia i recommend always to use the effect of Bancho first to special summon itself from hand and after that use the effect of Utopic Onomatopoeia, in that way your opponent will wait and target zs utopic sage or utopia double for negate and even if he use negate u can still make a good board.

 

I don't play numbers protection because it's brick if i am going second, xyz change tactic need actual combo in hand to be used, i don't need these cards. 

Utopic slash + downerd magician is used for zeus with 6 materials, that's very powerful. Utopic slash can be used as follow up too, if u have dragonar without materials u can summon utopic slash on top for zeus.

Tip: Crossout designator can be used only going first.

For budget versions, just cut droplet and i think u are ready to go, if is not enough u can replace evenly matched too, if is not enough then target lightning storm too, number 90 can be replaced by number 23 or 22 as last resorts

deck_description:
Myutant Ghoti post the Darkwing Blast Ghoti support. Solid Anti-Meta, no Dark or Light monsters for Bystials, Banish-okay for Tear and Floo, good end board with solid negates, powerful extra deck monsters.

Use Myutants to set up boards while banishing the Ghoti level 2s. Use Myutant negates and banishes to stop opponent plays, threaten Deep Beyond with Level 2s. Use ST-46 to search Cry for either pops with Synthesis, or negates with Ultimus (if available). 

If Ixeep becomes available from either Distant Deepest Depths, Gold Sarc, or a Myutant/Snop Banish; use to start Ghoti plays. Most common: Ixeep + 2 > Arionpos > Zep > Askaan/Whale > Arionpos 1, Askaan/Whale 2 > Banish Ask or Destroy Whale, Grab Snopios from Arion (Banishing Arion) > Ask banish to special, Snopios to interrupt with remaining 2 Fish in grave. 

Mist and Royal Decree personal preference, good for going against Labrynth or Eldlich. Arsenal/Mist + Royal Decree shut down most trap deck plays.

Spright Elf can summon both M-05 and either Ghoti level 2 during opponents turn. Can get the search from M-05, or the Synchros from Ghotis (only required to be special summoned during opponent's turn, do not have to be banished except Zep)

Chengying a staple in Ghoti, runs off the banishment well. Ruddy Rose to banish graveyards, can activate D.  Shifter after. Synthesis + Level 2 GHoti makes End Punisher, after Myutant Mutant very little chance your opponent can out PEP. Cut Guoglim for other staple Extra monsters, shut as Knightmare Unicorn or Baronne.

Other side deck options; Dimensional Fissure (Anti-meta), Crossout Des (Imperm shuts down Myutant very hard, good to keep that from happening), Lancea (Evenly), Called By (Ash, Droll, etc.)
New deck to try out the big boy

Adamancipator is my favorite deck which is struggling a lot with last banlists so I have been trying to find ways to get to a consistent end board.

The expected end board of this deck is Avramax(or Apollousa) + Naturia beast + baronne/Chengying + (koa'ki guardian sometimes).

What I like on this deck is that the only hand trap that does damage is Nibiru which is not currently on meta and I can use fissure/shifter without hurting a lot. On my decklist you can switch the hand traps and use what you prefer the most. Now on extra deck stuff get serious because space is limited. So from my experience I can say that these cards are the most usefull to be played as main or you can pick some from the side deck.

-

How to play this deck:

You begin with an adamancipator( you can use doki doki or cartorhyn to help with hand traps or get an adamancipator on board) and want to special summon Flint Crager on board so that you can send from the extra deck to GY Skullgar in order to get fossil fusion at hand. By filling the board with monsters with adamancipator effects probably you will be at a state where you can summon Naturia beast + Raptite + 2 monsters to link summon Cross-sheep. Then use fossil fusion to summon the other fossil by banishing Rock band Xenoguitar which can send to the grave(and after this to special summon Revival Golem). With sheep effect you special summon Adama Analyzer from the GY and then link to Masquerena -> Avramax and Synchro to Baronne de fleur and end your turn.

I hope you could understand the way to play this deck because the whole combo is big and can't be explained easily.
