deck_excerpt: The graveyard is dominating the metagame... Who you gonna call? EXOSISTERS!!!
deck_description:
Exosister is a deck specifically designed to counter a graveyard meta. Today (as with most meta over the course of Yugioh history), the meta is dominated by the Graveyard with all the Tearlaments, Ishizu, Runick, Bystial and Spright cards running around! With literally almost every deck dependent on GY interaction, it is now time for the beautiful combat nuns to exorcise the evils in the graveyard - The EXOSISTERS!

The Exosister gimmick is to transform their singular maindeck monster cards that are on the field into their power-up XYZ Extra Deck forms with various on-summon effects that lock out the graveyard for the turn. Their effects range from "neither player can activate effects in the GY" (Asophiel), "neither player can summon from the GY this turn" (Kaspitell), "monster negate" (Gibrine) and "banish" (Mikailis). To top it all off, a powerful board breaker and OTK enabler (almost like Accesscode) joined the Exosister Extra Deck lin-up in Dimension Force - Magnifica! Magnifica can non-target banish a card on the field and attack TWICE! That means she is 5600 damage on-board, or 7200 damage with Gibrine's attack increase effect - meaning that OTK can happen very quickly with this deck once an ideal boardstate is achieved.

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

 

 

COMBOS AND GAMEPLAN


Not only is this deck beautiful and fun - it is relatively simple to use! There is minimal complex combos or resource management. All you do is slap down some staple foodgates/boardbreakers, summon powerful monsters and OTK!

Watch the opposing Tearlament player's face contort in pain as you chain Dimension Shifter or activate Necrovalley! Laugh as you slap down one of your many blind second field wipes on your opponent's established board that they've worked so hard to create! Missing a card? You can dig into your deck with Pot of Prosperity for 6 since you don't really need most of your Extra Deck!

Going first or second, this is the simple common combo this deck uses:

1. Get two Exosisters on field to summon Kaspitell.

2. Activate Kaspitell effect to search for another maindeck Exosister monster to facilitate the summon of Mikaelis. (Usually its Martha. If you already used Martha to summon Kaspitell, grab an extender to normal summon + special summon -> Mikaelis).

3. Use your two Exosister monsters on-field to summon Mikaelis. Banish a card on-field as needed.

4. Activate Mikaelis' effect to search for an Exorsister spell/trap. (Going first, you'd generally you'd want to search Returnia to banish 1-2 cards on your opponent turn. If you already have it, get Vadis instead. Going second, you may want to search for Pax to summon another Exosister on field to push for game.)

5. Overlay Kaspitell + Mikaelis to summon Magnifica. Banish a card on-field as needed.

Going first, this combo from 1-2 Exorsister cards in-hand results in 4 banishes on your opponent's turn as well as a beefy hard-to-kill 2800 ATK monster!

Going second, this combo banishes 2 cards and can play through interruption especially if you've already simplified the game-state with your staple floodgates/boardbreakers to push for game!

In an ideal gamestate and empty opponent board, OTK is achieved through Magnifica + Jibrine. If you've saved your Magnifica from turn one, all you have to do is summon Jibrine to push for an OTK. Jibrine + Magnifica on an empty board is 9400 damage to your opponent's life points!

Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

 

 

GENERAL TIPS

  • While this deck is specifically tailored to hard-counter GY strategies, other decks that don't rely on graveyard is this deck's worst enemy - mainly Floowandereeze. Be sure to side in your Zombieworlds when facing them!
  • When going second against a Floowandereeze player and they have a set "Dreaming Town" on their field while you have Dark Ruler No More, you can play a funny mind game with them. Bluff the Evenly Matched in your hand by attempting to go to battle phase. This will force your opponent to activate Dreaming Town, since they can only activate it in the main phase. They will summon Apex Avian, so they can negate evenly matched. Now that you baited out their Apex Avian, you can now negate their entire board with Dark Ruler No More! (Trust me, this bluff works every single time, it's hilarious!)
  • When you opponent activates a card that moves a card out of the GY, like Bystial Magnumut or Kitkallos, chain Exorsister Vadis to give yourself two free monsters + powerful lingering floodgate effects/interruption that lock the GY or clear the field!
  • You can side out Called By the Grave alot of the time in this deck, since many cards in your arsenal render the GY useless/inaccessible anyways.
  • If you're going first, side in all your going first floodgates that often insta-win you the game. (Thanks for the free wins Anti-Spell and Gozen Match).
  • The cards in the Extra Deck commonly banished with Pot of Prosperity are: 1 copy of Mikaelis, 1 Zeus, 1 Bagooska, 1 Cowboy, 1 copy of Artemis, and 1 Tornado Dragon.
  • If you have plenty of extenders available for your mainline combo, try to save your normal summon for Sophia for an extra draw. Sophia can also be summoned from deck with Pax if Irene is somehow in your GY.

    Want to see the deck in action? Scroll to the very bottom for the Youtube video!

CONCLUDING COMMENTARY

The graveyard is dominating the metagame... Who you gonna call? EXOSISTERS!!!

Seriously though, I got tired of the mind-numbing graveyard chains that go 7+ at Locals. I go to Locals after work, and I'm too tired to do something that complex and intensive. So I started bringing Exosister to Locals, and my experience became so much more enjoyable! Sure, I may lose to that Floowandereeze guy, but hooooo BOY is it fun to floodgate out GY decks (SUCK IT TEARLAMENT ISHIZU) and win!

It's also really cool to wreck your opponents with cute combat nuns, every duel is like an episode of A Certain Scientic Railgun or Lycoris Recoil. Now I get to live out my "cute girls destroy bad guys" fantasy in Yugioh matches! :D

Hope you folks have as much fun as I do EXORCISING the graveyard!

Made in like 15 minutes. 

Basic idea is that one of Monarchs' problems is bricking too easily, so now with some new Water monsters with monarch stats, we can justify running Moray of Greed to hopefully brick less. Druiswurm is there as tribute fodder mainly, I'm not totally sold on it. Didn't add a side deck, but I think I would try to run the Umi Control cards in the side.

 

EDIT: Druiswurm removed, replaced with Kashtira Ogre for more WATER monsters, tribute fodder, and I guess Preparations is decent too?

This is a standard HERO Deck without the Evil HERO Package.

 

Main Deck Notes:

- You can cut the Honest Neos, which can make this build more consistent.

- Increase is at 1 because it does nothing in your hand, and you often have other lines of play on the rare occasion that you do draw it.

 

Extra Deck Notes:

- You can replace Dystopia with Dominance. If you do, you could replace Honest Neos or Plasma in the Main Deck with Destiny HERO - Dreadmaster. This can enable a combo where you pop it and your DPE during your End Phase. Then, you use Dominance as Chain Link 1, reviving DPE, Malicious and Denier, then DPE as Chain Link 2, reviving the Dreadmaster during the Standby Phase of your opponent’s turn. This will give your Destiny HERO Monsters Extra Protection, and on your next turn you can link off Denier and Malicious to make Cross Crusader and bring back the Dominance for extra damage.

 

Side Deck Notes:

- Lancea is just here for the future when Kashtira gets more support and starts seeing more play.

- Harpie’s and Lightning Storm are for backrow, need I say more?

- Rivalry of Warlords is a really nasty option going 1st because if you give your opponent Dark Angel they’re locked into Warriors.

- Different Dimension Ground is my anti-Tear tech of choice for when you can’t get Dark Law on the field.

- Evenly Matched. It’s Evenly Matched. It breaks boards.

Springans is insanely great with the new inclusion of Champian Sargas and Tallyho. This deck allows you to go into a cool neat endboard using only Field + Springans name. The Crystal Beast engine gives the deck another way to perform combo by nsing pegasus, pegasus equip crystal beast rainbow dragon, and crystal beast rainbow dragon summoning another pegasus. The deck also uses Rainbow bridge, which adds a crystal beast and golgonda to your hand, so you're basically playing 3 terraformings along with springans watch and springans booty, it's crazy!

Your endboard can vary, field + name ends up in Champ Sargas, regular Sargas, and either an xyz or I:P for unicorn, either way the deck is pretty versatile when it comes to either going first or second. The endboard not be as strong as Tearlament and Kashtira, but it does work! Try it out!

deck_description:
Hi all,

This is the deck I decided to build to play competitively. The list is kinda classic but is effective.

Main Deck Building thoughts

  • Handtraps : in addition to Dimension Shifter, I added Ash Blossom for her genericity and Infinite Impermanence for hard match-ups (Floowandereeze, which is basically our worst match-up)
  • No Exosister Arment and no Exosister Carpedivem : I don't like those cards and I prefer more generic cards to adapt to various situations.
  • Gozen Match : I decided to play this card in the Main deck, as this is a really good floodgate in the meta (for Floowandereeze, Spright) and as I don't have Evenly Matched currently. However, a Field package as a replacement could be a good choice aswell.

Extra Deck Building thoughts

This Extra deck has a classic composition aswell with specific choices :

  • Gagaga Cowboy for the Time (we easilly pay a lot of LP overall).
  • Number 41: Bagooska the Terribly Tired Tapir for the hard match-ups (Floowandereeze).
  • Lyna the Light Charmer, Lustrous => Selene, Queen of the Master Magicians => Accesscode Talker : some good package, especially when this is Dimensional Barrier.

Side Deck Building thoughts

As I told before, I made the choice to have the Field package in the Side Deck. To complete the side deck :

  • Psy-Frame Package is another good handtrap for the deck, to disrupt your opponent's interactions.
  • The other different choice is Lightning Storm (as I don't have Evenly Matched) as a good Go-Second card.

 

As usual, if you have questions or feedbacks/advices to share to improve this list, do not hesitate to ask it in the comments :)

deck_excerpt: Combo, 200iq, tier 0, ABC, Ojama, XYZ, Rouge
deck_description:
Ojama ABC going second deck.

START/COMBO

  1. Standby Phase - Play Forbidden Droplet. Ideally, you wanna discard Ojamagic, but anyone normal Ojamas, ABC, XYZ, and Armed Dragon LV3 are fine.  
  2. Main Phase 1 - Summon Ojama Blue by Rescue Cat, Ojamatch, or Normal Summoning Ojama Blue.
  3. Battle Phase - Run your Ojama Blue into your enemy. Grab Ojamatch and Ojamagic. Play Ojamatch for Ojama Blue and repeat until you have at least 6 Ojamas in your hand, field, or graveyard, and 2X Ojamassimilation. 
  4. Main Phase 2 - Use Ojamassimilation and target ABC-Dragon Buster. Use ABC to Summon Saryuja Skull Dread. Use the second Ojamassimilation to target XYZ-Dragon Cannon. Use XYZ to Summon XYZ-Dragon Cannon. Special Summon ABC-Dragon Buster from your extra deck with its effect. Sacrifice XYZ-Dragon Cannon and ABC-Dragon Buster to summon A-to-Z-Dragon Buster Cannon.
  5. End Phase - Just end. you have a 4000 attack, unlimited omni negate card that can finish the game next turn by attacking 6 times*.

EXTRA

Throughout the Combo, you can pop your opponent's cards, with ABC-Dragon Buster and nightmares if you choose to not play Saryuja Skull Dread.

Ideally, you want 1 extra monster alive after the battle phase so Saryuja Skull Dread can get the link 4 effect and reset your hand.

When the ABC cards are sent to the graveyard, their float effects will trigger giving you potentially extra value.

Tech cards

  1. Prohibition - used for hand traps mainly but can be useful against other tech cards like Nibiru, the Primal Being and Gameciel, the Sea Turtle Kaiju 
  2. Draws. Upstart Goblin, One Day of Peace, Pot of Prosperity You can replace them with alternatives.
  3. XYZs- Both Sky Cavalry Centaurea and Number 64: Ronin Raccoon Sandayu is used if all else fails and you really want to still play the game. Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder - honestly a very niche situational card. used with Sky Cavalry Centaurea and Number 64: Ronin Raccoon Sandayu.
  4. Nightmares- Situationally good if you don't have board answers. Knightmare Phoenix for back row, Knightmare Cerberus for boss Monsters, and Knightmare Unicorn for everything else. 
  5. Link Spider- Only used for Nightmare co-link or extra link value at main phase 2.
  6. Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess - Strong Card in General. used instead of Saryuja Skull Dread if you want extra protection against Nibiru, the Primal Being 
  7. Bujinki Ahashima - used just before Sky Cavalry Centaurea and Number 64: Ronin Raccoon Sandayu for extra value in a lost game.

Side Deck

  1. Nibiru, the Primal Being - Strong Going Second card in General. typically used in matchups where you struggle to break the board with only Forbidden Droplet 
  2. Ojama Pink - decent going first card. Against swarm decks that need all their monster zones, this can block a lot of combos. Good with Ojamagic.
  3. Zombie World - Niche but important going first card. Game-breaking for decks that require one type like D/D/D and Sword Soul.
  4. Lightning Storm - Against people who still use back roll. going second card.
  5. Triple Tactics Talent - Versatile card that behaves similarly to Called by the Grave and Prohibition. Used for matchups that you can't win. (Check Common Questions).

Common Questions.

Winning

Unlikely. This is more of a rouge/non-meta/fun deck at best. Is it possible to win against the current meta decks? Yes. But is it probable? No. The current Yugioh Meta game is fast and lockdown-heavy. If you go first with this deck you will die before your second turn. If you go second, you have to board clear omni negates, spells, traps, and hand-traps. Against a lot of meta decks, it's less so about you getting lucky to win but your opponent getting unlucky for you to have a chance to get lucky and win.

Counters

Dark Ruler No More - It is the single best counter to this deck. if your opponent plays this card after your A-to-Z-Dragon Buster Cannon, you have lost there is no real way around it outside of Prohibition and praying.

Gameciel, the Sea Turtle Kaiju, Lava Golem, The Winged Dragon of Ra - Sphere Mode, etc - the latter can be countered by having only A-to-Z-Dragon Buster Cannon, but Gameciel, the Sea Turtle Kaiju is death without Prohibition.

Prohibition

Prohibition is your only out in a lot of situations, but it is hard to play. You have to know what your opponent is playing, what they have in hand right now, you have to draw it and it is vulnerable. the ideal targets are Fairy Tail - Snow, Dark Ruler No More, and Gameciel, the Sea Turtle Kaiju.

Hand Traps

I don't particularly like hand traps, but ethics aside, you don't really need it in this deck. The entire purpose of this deck is to bring out A-to-Z-Dragon Buster Cannon. Stopping your opponent doesn't further the goal, it just makes it easier. Putting in cards like Effect Veiler, Fairy Tail - Snow, or Infinite Impermanence means taking out Forbidden Droplet or Prohibition, cards that are more important in the deck.

 

Author's note

I always liked Ojamas. I think they are goofy and beating your opponent with 2-star normal monsters is very satisfying. realistically this deck is probably trash, but I would appreciate any opinions, advice, and ideas to make it better.

Thank you for taking your time and reading this soup of words.

Don't be too jealous

deck_excerpt: Bringing to light good tech cards for Dark World, have a look!!
deck_description:
A typical Danger! Dark World deck with a twist.

The 10 extra cards in the main deck are not a cause for concern because once the combo is finished, you are left with around 15-20 cards in your main deck.

Tech cards and why I chose them:

MAIN DECK

Monsters

Dicelops : Used to discard your cards or disrupt your opponent's strategy by discarding a card from their hand (effect chosen at random).

Zalamander Catalyzer : Choose which Dark World monster you discard. Can return to the hand.

Dark Spirit of Banishment : Floats, goes really well with level 8 fiend monsters in the current deck.

Astral Kuriboh : Quick rank 4 or 8.

Danger!? Jackalope? : Chose this over Danger!? Tsuchinoko? because of its ability to go into rank 4s more easily.

Spells

Gold Sarcophagus : Consistency boost, used to search & special summon Genta, Gateman of Dark World.

Branded Regained : Consistency boost, returns your banished monsters to the deck to draw 1.

 

EXTRA DECK

Number 92: Heart-eartH Dragon : Chose this over Number 100: Numeron Dragon because of its ability to banish. Up to preference though.

Masterking Archfiend : Consistency boost, can add to the hand, special summon or shuffle back into the deck fiends sent to GY (chosen randomly).

 

SIDE

Masked HERO Dark Law : Used against decks that rely upon the graveyard to make their plays.

Fire Cracker : Combo takes too long to do so you can burn to win with time on game 2. Feel free to switch to whatever you want if you're not playing physically.

Number 59: Crooked Cook : Can become unstoppable if summoned with Astral Kuriboh as material.

Fallen of Albaz & Mirrorjade the Iceblade Dragon : Easy summon of a big body that also has a built-in nuke. Also functions as a super poly. Good for going second, or if you summon Ceruli, Guru of Dark World to your opponent's field.

Shuffle Reborn : Can help rebuild your board, re-use cards like The Gates of Dark World and draw 1 card in the process.

 

EDIT: Removed Amorphage Goliath, Danger! Bigfoot!, Danger! Thunderbird!, Danger!? Tsuchinoko?  & Neko Mane King  as they were too bricky. Also changed ratios of some cards and added The Fabled Cerburrel & Lucent, Netherlord of Dark World (synchro Groza, Tyrant of Thunder)

deck_name: Labrynth Lady of Lament Post CYAC
deck_description:
This Deck wants to make full use of Lady Labrynth of the Silver Castle and Lovely Labrynth of the Silver Castle to control the field with the Lady of Lament monsters facilitating your Traps.

3 Lady Labrynth of the Silver Castle and 1 Lovely Labrynth of the Silver Castle. Lady Labrynth is untargetable and indestructible, and it can even Summon itself from your hand, so you can just search her rather than Summon her off of a Welcome Labrynth Trap. She also sets Traps from Deck contrary to Lovely Labrynth who sets Trap from GY. Lovely Labrynth is what you are usually Summoning off of your Welcome Labrynth Traps and the Field Spell and it helps recur Traps and acts as hand destruction. 3 Lilith, Lady of Lament who is a Quick Effect to Tribute a DARK monster and has your opponent randomly set 1 of 3 Traps of your choice from Deck. 3 Alice, Lady of Lament who can Summon back a Lady of Lament monster from GY on Normal Summon and when she is Tributed, she can add 1 Fiend whose ATK and DEF equal 2000 in total. This can add any Lady of Lament or even Labrynth Stovie Torbie. 2 Labrynth Chandraglier which acts as a Level 3 DARK Fiend for Ties of the Brethren, but it does have the Labrynth effect of setting a Labrynth Spell/Trap from Deck and it adds itself back. 1 Tour Guide as another Level 3 Dark Fiend for Ties, but she can Summon your 1 Doomdog Octhros which searchs any Level 8 Fiend from Deck when it is sent from field to GY. This gets Lady Labrynth who can just Summon herself from hand. 2 Labrynth Stovie Torbie which has the Labrynth effect of setting a Labrynth Spell/Trap from Deck and recurring itself, and it can be searched off of Alice.

3 Ties of the Brethren which usually is used to Summon Lilith, Alice, and/or Doomdog Octhros to fuel Lilith's effect to search Traps, search Lady Labrynth, and search another Lady of Lament of Stovie Torbie. 1 Labrynth Labyrinth which can be searched off of your small Labrynth monsters and it acts as removal and it recurs Fiends. 3 Pot of Extravagance for draws. 3 Infinite Impermanence, 3 Torrential Tribute, 1 Trap Trick, 3 Big Welcome Labrynth, 3 Welcome Labrynth, 2 Compulsory Evacuation Device, and 2 Archfiend's Ghastly Glitch. Imperm is negation. Compulse, Torrential, and Glitch are removal which trigger all of your Labrynth effects. Welcome Labrynth and Big Welcome Labrynth are 6 extra copies of Lady Labrynth and Lovely Labrynth. You always want those in rotation which is why we are maxing out on the Welcome Labrynths that Summon them.

Extra Deck is nothing much. Garura, N'tss, Aggregator, Trouble Sunny, and Cambroraster are Ultimate Slayer/Dogmatika Punishment Targets with added effects. Garura draws a card, N'tss destroys a card, Aggregator negates a face-up card, Trouble Sunny sends a card, and Cambroraster protects set cards. Then we just have Knightmare Unicorn, Dharc the Dark Charmer Gloomy, and Salamangreat Almiraj. Almiraj is probably the most important one since it can Link off Doomdog to search Lady Labrynth.

Side Deck is 3 Lord of the Heavenly Prison if you are facing someone with a lot of backrow removal, EvilTwins Ki-sikil & Lil-la for Trouble Sunny, 3 Ultimate Slayer, 3 Lightning Storm, the second Trap Trick, 2 Dimensional Barrier, and 2 Dogmatika Punishment.
The full detailed version such as combo guide is available on Youtube

deck_description:
Jan 7 2023 BLS Tournament

7th place out of 153 players in the swiss round

Ended: Top 32

After Jan 1 OCG banlist

 

Cards Highlight :

Vivid Tail + Skill Drain  -  activating monster effects under skill drain

Labrynth Chandraglier or Labrynth Stovie Torbie discarding Vivid Tail  -  Vivid Tail immediately after being discarded to the GY can be chained on top of face cards to dodge targeting (e.g. Arianna the Labrynth Servant being targeted by Infinite Impermanence can be bounced back and dodge negation)

Labrynth Archfiend   -  Beat Obelisk by 400 atk

 

Cards explained:

No Anti-Spell Fragrance  -  Figured too many continuous traps and Imperial Iron Wall is better at stopping Runicks

Eradicator Epidemic Virus  -  Going against Runicks, Sky Striker, Trap Trick and Mirror matchups

Dark Ruler No More  -  Combo used for Evenly Matched . However, he didn't have enough sleeves to place more Evenly Matched

Different Dimension Ground  -  Counter Grass and Ishizu decks

Rivalry of Warlords in the side deck  -  in case Gozen Match and Skill Drain are not enough

Gozen Match  -  There's a larger pool of multiple attribute decks.

Card of Demise  - There are 47 cards in the main deck. Low chance of drawing both Pot of Extravagance & Card of Demise in the first 5/6 draws. High risk but high rewards.

Vivid Tail  -  Presents more plays than Compulsory Evacuation Device. Recycle cards, control no card Evenly Matched condition, Target avoidance, Skill Drain avoidance, same-turn plays, Labrynth's trigger effect of monster leaving the field (the second effect of Vivid Tail works as well) and works well with the Ishizu milling engine.

Solemn Strike  -  Combo decks have a higher chance of running just hand traps than Harpie's Feather Duster or Lightning Storm. They are more likely to stop trap plays via monster's negates(e.g Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring, Baronne de Fleur ) than back-row sweeps.

Underworld Goddess of the Closed World  -  Geomathmech Final Sigma and other similar cards with an unreachable attack or indestructible counter.

Labrynth Archfiend  -  End game plays, clutch card, board flooding, scalable attack (counter cards like Obelisk the Tormentor). The special summoning condition works with continuous traps.

This deck, as any zombie deck, prefers going first but it can go second as well. That's why it mains 3 droplets, 2 DRNM and some extender spells like Vendread Charge (it runs only zombies in the main deck), One for One (give access to 3 monsters) and foolish burial.

The goal of this deck is ending on a Vendread Ritual boosted by Houndhorde+Revenants effects, an Extra Deck monster with negate or removal, and the Vendread Trap. 

The best endboard possible would be Revendread Slayer+Chengying/Baronne/Dawn Dragster+Vendread Reorigin ft. Scar in the GY. Here you can banish 2 cards (1 S/T+1 monster) form your opponent's field (Quick Effect), banish 2 more cards without targeting with Chengying as a consequence (or a negate if Dragster/Baronne), and you still have a non-destruction removal with Reorigin which can trigger Scar effect. Therefore your opponent lost 5 cards while you got 2 more monsters on field (Scar+Token) with 2 more potential floating effect (Scar+Slayer). Baronne is a safer choice than Chengying because once it is summoned you can avoid a potential nibiru and an omninegate is still better overall to stop devastating cards like Evenly Matched. As I said it is the ideal endboard, Often you'll have to choose between the Trap and the Synchro though the double boosted Ritual is always guaranteed. Synchro option is obviously scarcer because you need to hard draw a tuner.

Example with Synchro+Ritual:

-Normal Uni-Zombie, send Mazera to GY

-Ritual Slayer with Origin by banishing Mazera, Special Summon Mazera by its effect

-Synchro Chengying/Baronne ( Uni-Zombie+Slayer), Slayer effect, add Ravenous, send Scar.

-Add 1 Vendread Charge by Scar effect, Use Charge on Mazera to Summon Houndhorde from Deck

-Ritual Summon Slayer from GY with Ravenous by using Houndhorde on field and Revenants from Deck.

3 card-combo, 2 quick effect banish+ 1 omninegate. But it dies to a single Droplet/DRNM.

 

A weaker but easier endboard:

-Ritual Slayer with Evolution by sending Scar, Add Reorigin by scar effect

-Norm any Zombie from hand, Link it away with Slayer to Summon Vampire Sucker, add 1 Ravenous and send Hounhorde with Slayer effect.

-Discard 1 Vendread card to summon Houndhorde from GY, Vampire Sucker draws 1 card, Ritual Slayer from GY with Ravenous by using Houndhorde+Revenants from Deck

-Because you tributed a monster on field, you can revive Scar by banishing a zombie from GY, Link Summon Scar+Sucker to get Savior

-Add Ravenous from GY to hand with Savior, Set the Trap.

Therefore you have 2 quick banish, 1 free foolish burial in battle and 1 non-destruction removal which brings you 2 free bodies. You can still play even if you get kaiju-ed or DRNM/Droplet-ed. With a slightly better hand you can end on Yuki-Onna the Link-4 Mayakashi which is really annoying against decks which use a lot their GY and decks based on banished monster's effects like Weather Painter/Thunder Dragons/ Metaphys.

But then, what about Shiranui cards? Though they aren't that interesting on your first turn, Shiranui can be devastating on your second turn or later in the game when Vendread burnt all their ressources. If you manage to set the Shiranui Trap alongside the previous or just a boosted Slayer, you can destroy 2 cards on their field+1 additionnal face-up card if you banished the Spiritmaster, in addition, because you tributed Slayer, it will float and trigger Scar effect makes you a free body+another float in case your opponent get rid of it. Sad this Trap can't be searched easily.. You can also banish Squire from Deck instead of Spiritmaster  to just have more draw power and GY set-up. Shiranui Spectralsword is very interesting once in GY to summon Samuraisaga which can reach more than 5000 ATK and bypass big bodies. If destroyed, you can have Spectralsword back in your GY, to summon Sunsaga next turn #grind-game. Vendreads synergize well with Shiranui because they continuously banish Zombies from GY (Origin, Slayer, Scar, Core..) which trigger easily their effects. Furthermore, Solitaire is a good Normal Summon which can bring you Uni-Zombie or Glow-bulb following your gameplan, such as Squire=Immortal Dragon guaranteed=foolish burial.

 

Miscellaneous:

-Battelord is a really underrated card which can save you from nibiru or many annoying effect monsters. Your opponent has to get rid of this card, otherwise you call Spell vs Runick or Trap vs Labrynth and their turn is over. Very good bait card.

-The Link-3 Mayakashi can negate the effects of a monster on field and be used to summon back Felgrand, which banish 1 monster on field/GY and also negate 1 monster effect on field.

-Vampire Fascinator is really good in case you get Ash-ed or Belle-ed during your turn: If Link Summoned you can revive your opponent's Ash/Belle to your field, and use it as an extender. Its second effect steals your opponent's monster and trigger Scar's revive, your oppoent lose 1 monster and you get 2.

-Avramax is easier to make in this deck than Borrelsword, it is a good go first endboard option and a good out to untargetable/unnaffected annoying beatsticks.

-Underworld Goddess is a must-have because this deck can easily bring 4 monsters on board+it's another out to annoying towers.

-Charge sends to GY as cost, so if your opponent doesn't chain immediately, you can protect Uni-Zombie/Battelord/Squire from Imperm. It's also an "out" to Skill Drain, if you have a Vendread with Houndhorde effect, you can target Skill Drain to banish it then you chain Charge to it, ez.

 

Strenghts:

-Withstand very well against destruction removal

-Has a lot of removal options, good board breaker

-Quite consistent

-Good grind-game

-Has good extenders

-Reacts well against DRNM/Kaiju

-Can play through Nibiru

-Can OTK

 

Weaknesses:

-Weak against any removal not destruction-related (banish, bounce..)

-Burn quickly its ressources if it can't access the Shiranui/tuner engine.

-As any zombie deck, Not resilient, cannot play through 2+ hantraps

-Cannot play through Shifter/D-Fissure or any card like that.

-No Draw power

-Dies from Evenly Matched if no Baronne

-No in-archetype boss monster, too reliant on the Extra Deck

-Need too many cards to start a combo (3-card combos in most cases)

Once upon a time, there was this brilliant idea called mhAsTeR RHuLe Tr33, to which all kinds of disasters were allowed to walk the earth and sank in the moggy swamp water of false optimism and depravity. From poorly written/drawn anime adaptions of ArcV to the worst way to introduce a new summoning mechanic without giving free American Spirit Cigarettes at Woodstock-99, it seems we are stumbling back to 2005 at this point. All is said however when we suddenly got some nice gems during this time. Such treasures found in the rubble of debris and decay from MhAsta RHuL Tr33 included Tellarknights and Shaddolls. From here on is where one of my first decks of Shaddoll - Tellarknights came to be.

 

   How the tangence of "El Shaddoll Construct" and the Tellarknights came to be is from the usual Shaddoll business of doing what they do best. Meanwhile, the Tellarknights are the backbone by providing monsters like "StellarKnight Constellar Diamond" and "Cyber Dragon Infinity" through what I will call "the Ptolemaeus method" (a method that XYZ summons Tellarknight Ptolemaeus using a collective of LV4 monsters to rank up into crucial Rank 5 monsters, excluding "Numbers"). I would call it one of the tankiest combinations for deck-making for even mAhstA RhULe tR33 standards. To this day though, I don't honestly know what to say considering that MR🌳 was filled with nothing but the chaos that our corporate overlords sealed in a plastic container in an old company fridge for at least 10 years.

deck_excerpt: My third Anti-Meta Deck (circa 2018, I think). This deck is a little rough, not exactly happy with it.
deck_description:
Pretty much the same as Anti-Meta 2 but with more support to Vanity's Field & Majesty's Fiend with Sinister Yorishiro (I added Summoned Skull for that purpose but it was the easiest choice, not the best choice) & able to tribute on your oppoents turn with Escalation of the Monarchs (paired with The Monarch's Stormforth is a dirty dirty move & paired with Spell Canceller is super cheap too). Power of the Guardians has become a stable in my decks now due to the PURE hatred it causes, I have had players surrender at the very sight of this card. I added Card Destruction because with Necrovalley it potentially ruins all plays (think Blue-Eyes decks). I removed Mystic Mine for The Winged Dragon of Ra - Sphere Mode as honestly, I think it's more annoying to deal with & removes all the cards the field support cards, I had in my past decks. Dark Hole is an interesting addition, as it could be used (and negated) with Starlight Road for Stardust Dragon. Vision HERO Witch Raider was a really fun card addition with all the traps & her effects are incredibly strong. Before I shelved this deck, I was experimenting with Utopia as it was solid idea to having stronger characters with decent effects. 

The main goal is completely stall your opponent by having Jinzo (No Traps), Vanity's Fiend (No Special Summons), Majesty's Fiend (No activated monster effects) & Spell Canceller (No Spells) on the field at the same time while annoying them the entire time.

deck_excerpt: Noble Knights, King Arthur Lore, Artorigus, Combo
deck_description:
Ah it's Noble Knights! Isolde turbo right?.... Yes but there's more then just her. What if I tell you this Deck successfully implements every Noble Knight from the King Arthur Lore into one Deck. Noble Knights look a bit flat on the outside but it's a Combo Deck in it's core so let's start going into Detail:

 

The Starters

In such a type of Deck it's important to see who the Starters for your Combo are. Noble Knight Medraut is by far the number one Combo Starter. Like many Noble Knights he's treated as a normal Monster until you equip a Noble Arms Equip to him. Then he gains 1 Level changes to Dark attribute and can special one Noble Knight from Deck in defense (If he's the only Monster you control). Also he destroys the Noble Arms Equip after. 

But that's were the Noble Arms equips start working. Once per turn if they are destroyed they can reequip to one Noble Knight on the field for example the one you just special summoned triggering it's effect in the process. 

Many cards get you to this Starting Point. Merlin and Heritage of the Chalice being the best ones for that. Other Starting Combinations with Noble Knight Brothers and such are there too but less efficient. They become Plan B and you will see the rest for yourself should you decide to pick up this Deck. 

 

What comes next? 

With Medraut the World lies in front of you. Every Noble Knight you can Special has a specific role and that's why I will shortly list up what for everyone is there from top to bottom: 

Laundsallyn

Gives access to a Rank 5 XYZ summon without a second Noble Arms Equip. He can also search for another Noble Arms Card by offering a tribute. 

Eachtar

Gives access to a Rank 5 XYZ summon without a second Noble Arms Equip and makes the Summon and on summon effect unchainable for the opponent. Together with Laundsallyn they are recurring Threats from the GY every turn for a little cost.

Pellinore 

Enables a Monster Destruction with a Draw 1 on top of it. The lost Noble Arms Equip can then be retrieved with the Rank 4 Artorigus XYZ summon.

Gawayn

He's pretty much just a Name and is better of in your Hand to use it's special summon effect. 

Peredur

Very useful to go into Isolde because the lost Noble Arms Equip can be returned to the Hand through his effect and open more options after Isolde special summoned one Noble Knight onto the field.

Drystan

Protects other Noble Knights with less then 1800 ATK from attacks and targeting and thanks to Medraut he destroys one face up card on summon if you reequip the Noble Arms to him. 

Iyvanne

Can summon one token for free which enables a easy Isolde summon without loosing the Noble Arms Equip on field and furthermore sets up a Rank 4 XYZ summon with the Help of Isolde. A 500 ATK Boost for all Noble Knights is the Cherry on top.

Borz 

He can search 3 Noble Arms Cards from deck, get one to Hand and mill the other two randomly. Choosing the Trap Until Noble Arms are Needed Once Again sets up 3 Quick effect special summons from Deck at any time as well as a free draw and changes the order of the top cards of your Deck. 

Bedwyr

Mills one Noble Arms Equip from Deck to GY and as Quick Effect is able to reequip a Equip to another Monster once while he's on field. Good to use in Combination with Drystan as interruption when the setup is already there. 

Gwalchavad

Can recycle one Noble Knight from the GY back to your Hand and destroys one Noble Arms equip after that. When the Setup with Bedwyr, Brothers, Isolde and Drystan is there you can create a nice little Ressource and Destruction Loop with build in Targeting and attack protection thanks to Drystan.

Brothers

He has 2400 DFF as a Level 4. He can Recycle 3 Noble Arms/Knight Cards back into the Deck to Draw 1 Card and on Normal summon only he can special up to 2 more Noble Knights from Hand enabling a 3 Material King Custennin to Bounce up to 3 Cards from the opponent and potentially Rank Up into a Artorigus. 

Custennin

If he's used for a Extra Deck summon you gain an additional normal summon. Very useful if one of the Noble Knights you wanted to special summon from Deck is already in your Hand. 

Artorigus

Just a Vanilla 1800 Beatstick but it's good to get him into grave early to setup Lady of the Lake or Avalon. He's the easiest way to access your Level 5 Synchro Monster with Lady of the Lake combined.

 

That's nice and all but what's the payoff? 

The big payoff in this Deck is the Rank 5 XYZ Monster Sacred Noble Knight of King Artorigus or in similar fashion the Rank 4 XYZ Artorigus, King of the Noble Knights. Both can equip themselves with up to 3 Noble Arms Equip spells from the GY when they are summoned. Thanks to Isolde you will be able to freely choose which ones you want. 

The Rank 4 can destroy Spell and Traps on the Field up to the Number of Noble Arms Equips you control. The Rank 5 one can destroy one Monster on the field and if he's send to the GY he specials another Noble Knight back from the GY.

The easy to achieve Dream is a 4k Beater with Targeting protection and the ability to prevent destruction twicr per turn. You can add a Destroy 1 Set Card from the opponent by sacrificing 500 ATK and Direct attacking by paying 500 LP depending on which Noble Arms you choose on top of that. 

Since the Noble Arms can reequip themselves once destroyed, be recycled with Peredur and the Artorigus bosses you can repeat every effect easily 4 times every turn. So how does: Gain 2000 LP and Destroy 4 set Cards from the opponent sound? 

 

Just a little more Spice

You might notice there are a few Monsters which are not Noble Knights. Merlin earlier mentioned summons any Noble Knight from Deck but he can also at quick effect speed no matter when XYZ or Synchro summon using Monsters on field. He turns up the OTK potential of this deck to 11.

Morgan is a handtrap which acts as Omni Negate which is strong but needs a little setup to work.

Gwenhwyfar is a Noble Arms Equip disguised as Monster and can recycle itself every turn back onto a monster as equip Spell. She gives a one time destruction protection for Light attribute and win every Battle before Damage Step ability for Dark Attribute. Also a little 300 ATK are for both Attributes.

Lady of the Lake like earlier mentioned is there to get the Synchro 5 onto the field. He is the only card which can search any Noble Knight/Noble Arms card including the 3 Noble Knight Spells. 

 

The Problems

Wow this Deck sounds like a meta contender for sure.... yeah no it's not all good here too. If the opponent removes every Noble Knight from the field, you can't reequip the Noble Arms cards and loose important advantage. Loosing Artorigus with 5 Equips through a Kaiju hurts a lot too and often leaves you open for a lethal strike. 

If the opponent understands the importance of Medraut and gets rid of him or negates him you can only use your weaker Plan B starters which can't build up a formidable Board that fast. A good Medraut Starter Hand mills half your Deck turn one. Brothers, Gawayn and Custennin can't get to that position alone sadly. 

 

Final Words

It looks like I wrote way to much but really I just scrapped the bottom of the Barrel. When I picked this Deck up I didn't think there's so much hidden Combos and Potential within this Archetype. If you are a player who likes more Complex/Deep strategies this Deck is made for you. 

Just recently at time of writing this Deck profile I reached Diamond V league in Master Duel using only Noble Knights. Not many know about this Deck at all and it wins against many unprepared opponents.

Overall Rating: ★★★☆☆☆

deck_excerpt: The bane of Masterduel's Bo1 ladder and the current best stall deck - Floodgate Runick! With this, YOU ARE THE FINAL BOSS!
deck_description:
The bane of Masterduel's Bo1 ladder and the current best stall deck - Floodgate Runick! With this deck, YOU ARE THE FINAL BOSS!!!

Stop your opponent from playing with floodgates, banish their deck along with their "outs" to your stranglehold, and control their plays with your Runick spells! All this happens while you maintain insane advantage drawing 2-5+ cards per turn, ensuring you're always ahead in the resource game!

Watch your ladder opponents twist their faces in despair and horror as you flip over devastating floodgates like Skill Drain, Gozen Match and Rivalry of Warlords! Expect lots of easy games and quick surrenders with Floodgate Runick!

No in-depth guide will be included for this deck, since it doesn't have any linear combos.For being such a strong deck, it is incredibly easy to play. Floodgate Runick is less about complex combo/decision making, and more about resource management/strangling your opponent to death (in-game of course lol).

The strategy is to establish Runick Fountain, draw cards as much as possible, and stop your opponent from playing with your floodgates and Runick quick-play spells.

Laugh as you MONKE-FLIP unfair floodgates, draw a million cards and deck out your opponent all the way to Diamond 1!

GLHF Duelists!

Fabled? Ahhh it's on of these Hidden Arsenal trash piles that do nothing right? NO! Unlike some strange subjects that came out of Hidden Arsenal Fabled is one of the Archetypes that is very much functional.

But beware playing Fabled takes a lot of practice since there's always at least 10 different ways to go within this Deck and one play can set you onto a path which you can't change after you decided to walk it. 

Let me explain more in Detail what this Deck is all about: 

 

The Starting Point

Almost every card is a Starter in this Deck which makes it difficult to pinpoint down one specific one. Your Goal is to summon multiple copies of Fabled Ragin while emptying your Hand to get to a wide lineup of Fabled Synchros or alternatively Cosmic Blazar Dragon and or Red Supernova Dragon. Almost every Fabled Monster is missing a once per turn Condition making big Combo setups very easy. 

To facilitate advantage onto the field cards like Fabled Krus and The Fabled Cerburrel exist which special themselves or another Monster onto the field when discarded. Monsters like Fabled Raven or Fabled Marchosia enable the discarding to trigger these effects. Every maindeck Fabled follows one of these 2 patterns. Helping to discard or wanting to be discarded. 

Here it's important to remember that Discarding is not Sending. Fabled Soulkius sends 2 cards to the GY so he won't trigger the Fabled effects, which you sometimes actually want. 

 

The Special Subject 

The Fabled Unicore has to get it's own paragraph here. It's one of only 2 Monsters existing the other being Cyber Blader which has the ability to negate everything if certain Conditions are met. And with everything I mean EVERYTHING! Since the effect acts as a permanent effect like Skill Drain for example it can negate Counter Traps, Super Polymerization and everything normally unrespondable and destroy these cards. 

To have this effect active both you and your opponent have to have the same amount of cards in their Hand. Thanks to the nature of Fabled Monsters it's best used as a agressive tool to go for game without being interrupted. Cards like Dianaira, Ragin, Andwraith, Leviathan and the Trap Treason can give this ability a nice twist and surprise the opponent during his turn too with correct setup.

Certainly a card to look out for but only if the Situation allows. Pro Tip: Summoning Unicore first turn and passing is not good within this Deck! 

 

The other Stuff to look out for

Dianaira changes the effect of the first Normal Spell activated from the opponent each turn to you discarding one card instead. Gallabas can Destroy Monsters by discarding cards without a Once per Turn. Cat Sith mandatory destroys one Face Up card if she's discarded. De-Synchro is mainly to loop Fabled Ragin more often but you can also De Synch an opponents Synchro Monster with it if you are desperate. 

Fabled Treason can also destroy your own face up cards or an opponents one, discard one of your cards and revive one Monster all written to be able to destroy your own Leviathan to Recycle any 3 Fabled Monsters back to Hand. Your big 3k LV10 Boss Monster Leviathan sadly misses timing sometimes if the opponent deals with him.

Andwraith Draws 2 and discards one but the opponent can discard one card to negate this effect. If he discards a Monster you can summon it to your side. Since Andwraith triggers on special summon he's a nice target to be brought back with Treason to force the opponents Hand and potentially unlock the perfect Unicore Lockdown.

 

Final Words

Fabled struggles to set up a strong Wall but can easily overwhelm the opponent in one turn through massive Special summoning. But winning with this Deck takes practice since there's a lot that can go wrong if you choose the wrong Monsters to bring to your field at the wrong time. It's almost like Math. 

Practicing this kind of Deck will reward you greatly with one easy to understand but very hard to master Deck. Give it a try if you feel up to take this challenge of a Deck. 

Overall Rating: ★★☆☆☆☆

LABYRINTH MUSKETEER COMPETITIVE DECK JANUARY 2023

MATCHES AND COMBOS BELOW

Principal

Vennominom e Vennominaga são as arma principais do deck. É dividida em duas fazes, primeiro é trazer Vennominom ao campo, chuva de cobras será essencial para envial-o ao cemitério e trazê-lo de volta com limite reverso ou monster reborn e espere pela ascensão da deusa serpente. Os sarcofagos dourados vão agilizar o deck, depois de 2 turnos você pode buscar uma das cartas centrais, chuva de cobras, limite reverso, monster reborn ou ascensão da divindade serpente caso você ainda não as comprou. Suborno obscuro será importante para contra-atacar a negação de ascensão da deusa serpente.

 

Os ajudantes.

Vennominom e Vennomimnaga precisam do cemitério alimentado de monstros répteis, e o arquétipo alien com seus efeitos de marcadores A, que permitem enfraquecer monstros,(semelhante aos marcadores de veneno, mas este é ativado apenas em batalha, e apenas contra aliens) destruir mágicas e armadilhas e destruir monstros, são muito mais atraentes do que os monstros peçonhetos que são um peso morto no deck. Eles vão fazer controle de campo, destruir mágicas e armadilhas, negar efeitos e matar os monstros grandes do seu oponente com os marcadores A enquanto você prepara a chegada de Vennominom e Vennominaga.

Um bom equipamento

Já que é um deck réptil, mudança de pele será inestimável, vai impedir que o monstro réptil equipado seja destruido na fase de batalha uma vez por tunro, e a cada vez que ele não for destruido em batalha contra um monstro com mais ataque, ela ganha 300 de ataque, até ficar mais forte que todos os monstros do advérsario. Embora Vennominom e Vennominaga possam banir um monstro réptil e reviver, ele voltam cada vez mais fracos, sendo vulneráveis a monstros com 2 ataques ou mais, então mudança de pele será muito importante, mas em caso de emergência, também pode ser usado salvar um alien.

Ajudantes do deck extra

Os aliens do deck principal ainda são monstros pequenos, o deck adcional expandirá suas opcões, e te dará monstros grandes. Já que o arquétipo alien tem um monstro sincro, usaremos tanto monstros sincro e xyz. Scrap archfiend e dark rebellion dragon são invocação mais genéricas, se você quer apenas um monstro forte, ou um simples number 39 utopia. Cosmic fortress Gol'gar vai limpar a zona de cartas mágicas e armadilhas do seu oponente, mas cuidado, vai limpar a sua também. Dragon Vermillion pode banir um monstro turner do cemitério e destruir um card no campo, mas esse efeito pode custar muito caro por banir um regulador, que você poderia recicla-lo com limite reverso ou monster reborn para fazer mais uma invocação sincro, você só vai poder recuperar o monstro regulador banido quando Dragon Vermillion for enviado ao cemitério por efeito de card. Coral Dragon é uma opção mais viável, já que você apenas descarta um card para dar alvo em uma carta no campo do oponente e destruí-la, (é uma ótima opção de viagem de Vennominom ao cemitério caso ele esteja na sua mão e você não esteja conseguindo invoca-lo por invocação tributo). E King Of The Feral Imps será ótimo para buscar mais dois répteis, por exemplo um Alien Ammonite para invocação sincro. Mas os use com tendo em mente que os marcadores alien não serão ativados quando eles lutarem, já que ninguém do deck extra é um monstro alien.

Considerações finais

Claro isso não é meta, mas eu gosto do que o arquétipo Venom poderia ser, pena que ele esteja no fundo do porão sem ter contato com um raio de luz do dia, e talvez nunca terá, mas é a minha contribuição para torna-lo mais jogável.

Necessidades

O arquétipo Venom precisa de suportes para ser pelo menos ok. A chave é Vennominaga, cuja invocação da carta armadilha pode ser cancelada por uma tonelada de monstros, e Vennominom não poder ser invocado especialmente por efeito de monstros é apenas um prego no caixão, limita a sua  invocação a especial apenas do cemitério e tributo. Vennominom pode reviver banindo um monstro réptil, mas volta mais fraco, se você não tiver meios acéssiveis de mandar répteis para o cemitério que não dependa de chuva de cobra, ele voltará apenas para morrer. Eu recriaria Vennominom para poder ser invocado especialmente por invocação de monstro (claro, o arquétipo precisaria de uma monstro que invoque especialmente répteis com um ataque baixo), Vennominom poderia ter um efeito rápido ou não de mandar um monstro réptil da sua mão e/ou deck para o cemitério. E como Vennomionm e Vennominaga precisam do cemitério alimentado de répteis, nada mais lógico do que o arquétipo precisar de monstros peçonhetos com efeitos variados no cemitério, como: invocação especial (para acesso rápido a Vennominom), buscador de cartas Venom, destruir monstros envenenados como faz o alien Stealthbuster, talvez monstros que tenham efeitos ao serem banidos  e monstros que enviem outros ao cemitério, já que o cemitério é a chave do deck, e claro, todos com efeitos de porem marcadores de veneno, que é a marca registrada do arquétipo, também, de condições diferentes de colocaram marcadores de veneno, o arquétipo Venom tem muito a aprender com o arquétipo alien, que é um deck Venom moderno.

fraquezas

Seja o arquétipo Venom atual ou o meu imaginário, ele ainda teria fraquezas incontornáveis a serem exploradas, como qualquer deck. Além das que eu já mencionei, cartas que mudam o atributo dos monstros no cemitério como Zombie world são fatais, Necrovalley não deixaria Vennominom e Vennominaga renascerem pelo efeito de banir um monstro réptil, cartas que impedem que monstros sejam enviados ao cemitério como macro cosmos também serão letais, assim como as que negam efeitos ativados no cemitério.
